title: beef rice soup(beef barley soup)
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir lightly and set aside.
Combine sugar, persimmon pulp, milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bread is done. Yields one loaf.

title: meatballs with light herb sauce(serves 4 to 6; under 200 calories)
directions: Broil meatballs 6-inches from heat source 5 to 6 minutes or until browned.
Drain on paper towel and set aside.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water; drain and rinse.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix well and stir into macaroni.
Add eggs, carrots, onion and pepper; mix well. Toss in cheese.
Chill overnight.
Serves 10 people.

title: fruit casserole
directions: Drain juice from fruits.
Save juice.
Put drained fruit in casserole dish.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter heavy large cookie sheets.
Melt shortening in heavy small saucepan over low heat.
Pour into large bowl and let stand until cool, but not set.
Mix in 1 cup sugar, molasses and egg.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger, salt and nutmeg in a small bowl.
Stir into shortening mixture.
Cover and refrigerate dough for 10 minutes.

title: passionate casserole
directions: Combine love and tenderness.
Set 2 candles on table; mix well.
Add man and woman.
Give woman roses; set mood and let nature take its course.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Roll steak in 1/4 cup flour and salt.
Pan-fry onions, mushrooms and garlic in fat for 5 minutes.
Add steak and brown evenly; then remove meat, onions and mushrooms from pan.
Combine 2 tablespoonfuls flour with drippings in the pan.
Add bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until thickened.
Add sour cream and heat slowly until gravy simmers.
Add beef and vegetables and heat for a few minutes.
Serve hot on cooked rice, toast or noodles.
This needs a tart accompaniment like spiced fruit or tossed salad.
Yield:
4 to 5 servings.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugars and eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 325°.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Cook cake by directions on box.
Poke holes in top of cake when done.
Pour milk and pina colada mix over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip.

title: english trifle(dessert)
directions: In
deep bowl, break up jelly rolls, pour fruit cocktail over rolls.
Pour
a
jigger
of sherry on and also pour liquid already made
Jell-O
on
all ingredients and let set, usually overnight. Next
day,
make instant pudding, let cool and pour over
set Jell-O.
Slice
banana
onto
pudding and whip heavy cream.
Pour over bananas.
To decorate, use colored sprinkles or maraschino cherries.

title: maple-walnut sticky buns
directions: To prepare pan, melt 1/4 cup butter in pan; add brown sugar and 1/4 cup maple syrup.
Heat, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with 1/2 cup of the walnuts.
In mixing bowl, stir together 3/4 cup of flour, yeast, white sugar and salt.
Add 1/3 cup butter and warm water.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 1/4 cup more flour; beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough more flour to make a soft dough.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Combine the vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and celery seed; bring to boil.
Let cool and pour over the cabbage, onion, green pepper and carrot.
Let stand overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Place
all
ingredients in blender and mix.
Shape into ball and roll in finely chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until firm. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers and pecans.
Chip cherries.
Melt marshmallows and whipping cream together and pour over mixture.
Mix well. Press into buttered pan or Bundt pan.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar, pumpkin and shortening. Add the egg and vanilla, mixing well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoonful onto well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen. Can be iced with Cream Cheese Frosting recipe.

title: butternuts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Let set in refrigerator until cold. Put hands in flour and shape dough into cocoons.
Bake in slow oven (250°) until done.
Take out and roll in powdered sugar. Delicious!

title: terri's knots
directions: In a large bowl, combine the dry ingredients.
Mix the margarine and anise into the dry ingredients.
Add the eggs and mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Take a small piece of dough (about 2 tablespoons) and roll with palm of your hand to form a long pencil shaped string.
Take an end of the string and make a loose, single knot.
Break the knot off of the string.
Space knots about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes or until bottom of cookie is light brown.
Cool.

title: thimbles
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and egg yolk.
Sift salt and flour together.
Add vanilla.
Dough will be sticky.
Refrigerate for awhile, if necessary.

title: squash bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
In another bowl, combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla, mixing well.
Stir in squash.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: fudge brownies(microwave)
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking dish (microwaveable).
In medium bowl, melt margarine and chocolate on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Stir until smooth.
Stir in sugar and vanilla, then eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, 1 cup walnuts, baking powder and salt. Spread batter in dish.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crush Doritos and put all but 1 cup in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown meat and onion.
Add taco seasoning and 1 cup water.
Let simmer a few minutes, then add refried beans and heat through. Place in pan on Doritos.
Add lettuce and diced tomatoes.
Top with rest of Doritos and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry delight salad
directions: Mix together.
After spreading, sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans on top.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil margarine, water and cocoa.
While still hot, add and mix by hand to cocoa mixture flour, sugar and salt, then add eggs, sour cream, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake in a jelly roll pan or use 2 (9 x 13-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: creole meat loaf(from 1975 edition)
directions: Put ground beef in a bowl.
Add rice, onion, green pepper, salt, thyme, egg and half of an 8 ounce can of tomato sauce.
Mix thoroughly, then shape into loaf and place in shallow baking dish. Set in preheated oven and bake for 1 hour.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Cream sour cream and sugar together.
Add eggs and seasonings; blend.
Add pecans; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Put whipped cream on top.

title: jim's hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions.
Mix in all other ingredients and cook for 3 hours in 375° oven.

title: mock chicken salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add chicken soup and blend well.
Add
other
ingredients and chill in refrigerator until congealed.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
(Peanut chunks will come to top.)
Cool before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked apple
directions: Cut a thick slice from top of apple and core.
Put sugar in center of apple.
Add cinnamon and raisins.
Wrap loosely in foil. Bake 30 minutes in campfire.

title: "lost horizon" chicken and walnuts
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except oil, in a mixing bowl.
Let sit for at least 20 minutes.
Pour oil in wok and bring to 375°. Place chicken mixture in wok and stir-fry chicken until it is firm in texture.
Serve immediately.
(Fresh stir-fried or steamed asparagus goes well with this dish.)

title: spicy grilled burgers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and make patties.
Grill until desired doneness.
Serve with avocado and Swiss cheese slices.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots until tender in salty water, 12 minutes or so. Drain. Mix all ingredients and chill.
Keeps well. Do not freeze.

title: creamy mushroom and ham ravioli
directions: Cook ravioli as directed on package; drain.
Melt margarine in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add pepper and mushrooms; stir-fry.

title: lemon glaze cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. While cake is baking, prepare glaze.

title: auntie till's light fruit cake
directions: Melt
butter;
beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients and pour into Bundt pan.	Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: charles' no fail potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes. Combine all ingredients. Mix electric mixer, mix well until smooth, approximately 10 minutes. Pour into a 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: ham and cheese eggrolls
directions: Purchase your favorite eggroll wrappers.
Place a thin slice of ham and Provolone cheese on a wrapper.
Fold and seal as directed on wrapper package.
Fry in oil until golden brown. Serve with honey mustard.

title: lobster stew
directions: In a large saucepan, combine lobster sauce and cornstarch. Stir in vegetables, garlic and seasonings.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add fish and lobster. Return to boil.
Simmer 7 to 10 minutes or until fish and lobster are cooked.
This is the creme de la creme.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hermits
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts and fruits.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce; simmer 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to directions and drain.
Spread half the noodles in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover half cottage cheese and half grated cheese. Spread all the meat sauce over cheese.
Layer remaining noodles, cottage cheese and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Bake the cake in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
When cake is ready, punch holes in cake.
Mix the Eagle Brand milk and caramel topping; pour over cake while cake is warm.
Cool completely.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Crush the Heath bars; sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: sunday night supper sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on hamburger bun.
Place slice of pineapple on top and the top with slice of American cheese.
Top with a maraschino cherry.
Bake in a 400° oven until cheese begins to melt.

title: mom's spareribs
directions: Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Then drain off fat.
Pour sauce over ribs and bake another 45 minutes or until done.
Turn ribs every 10 minutes and baste them with the sauce.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook onion with thyme in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except potatoes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch container.
Top with 1 cup crushed cornflakes.
Pour 1/4 stick melted margarine over this.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet rice
directions: Fill medium saucepan with water.
Bring to boil.
Add rice. When rice is half done, add sugar and evaporated milk, stirring often to keep from sticking.
Cook until becomes thick.
Cool before serving.
Can go with main dish or can be used as a dessert.

title: old fashioned cherry pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; mix thoroughly.
Add juice from cherries and cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and clear.
Add cherries, oleo and lemon juice. Let stand and make pastry.
Fill shell and top with remaining pastry.
Pierce the top and flute edges.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes or until done (top will be golden brown).

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, the onion, salts, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded tbsp into balls.
Place meatballs in ungreased baking dish, 8X8x2 inches.
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over meatballs.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake 45 minutes. Uncover, bake 15 minutes longer.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a saucepan, over medium heat, cook fruit until boiling.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine flour, 1 cup sugar, milk, baking powder and salt.

title: hot rotel chicken casserole
directions: Cook, cool and debone chicken.
Cut up in small pieces and layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Pour in a 10-inch pan or an iron skillet that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper together; drain.
Combine next 3 ingredients; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese and mixed vegetables; salt to taste.
Pour into a greased bake dish. Separate biscuits into 20 pieces; overlap biscuits around outside edge of dish.
Spread 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese in center of biscuits.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: dirt cups
directions: Crush cookies in zipper-style plastic bag with rolling pin or food processor.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed cookies.
Place about 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into each cup.
Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies. Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Decorate with gummy worms and frogs, candy flowers, peanuts and granola.

title: alice's carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Add sugar and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook at 355° for 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes.
After cake is completely cooled, spread topping.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add onion, milk, water and egg.
Roll in balls; cook in deep fat at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: oriental steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over steak.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 8 hours, turning occasionally. Drain steak, reserving marinade.
Baste steak with marinade while grilling. (Especially good with flank steak.)

title: vegetable bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter and Ritz crackers. Put in approximately 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish or casserole. Mix melted butter and Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans.
Spread over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour over nut mixture.
Heat butter and cream cheese.
Stir in powdered sugar. Spoon over cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not cut until completely cooled.
Delicious! This cake keeps for days; the longer the better.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger, then add taco seasoning as instructed on package.
In large mixing bowl, put in cut up lettuce and tomatoes.
Add beans, cheese and hamburger.
Just before serving, add Fritos and desired amount of Catalina dressing.

title: no bake strawberry short cake
directions: Wash strawberries and drain well.
Slice cake into 2 layers. Put Cool Whip on top of first layer.
Slice half of the strawberries and put on top of Cool Whip.
Add the second layer and spread top and sides with remaining Cool Whip.
Place strawberries on top and around cake.

title: tex mix
directions: Mix taco seasoning mix, mayonnaise and sour cream; set aside. Spread bean dip in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread taco mix on top of bean dip.
Layer onions, olives and tomatoes and top with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: thrifty pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add flour, then eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Bake in a greased steeple pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Keep oven door closed for 45 minutes before looking at cake.

title: lemon gooey
directions: Combine cake, melted butter and 1 egg.
Pat into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Break tamales into small pieces. Layer ingredients into a casserole dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas morning pizza
directions: Brown sausage, drain. Unroll crescent rolls and seal to the bottom of a 9 X 13 to form a crust. Spoon on sausage, sprinkle with hash browns. Top with shredded cheese. Beat together eggs, milk and pepper. Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Bake for 25-30 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: honey-fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate with honey over hot water.
Add salt.
Stir until smooth.
Spoon hot sauce over ice cream.

title: chicken casserole #1
directions: Combine butter and cracker crumbs. Spoon half the crumbs into a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Top with chicken. Combine sour cream, soup, broth, salt and pepper; pour over chicken and top with remaining crumbs. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef; drain excess fat. Boil noodles until tender.
In casserole dish, combine beef, noodles, soups, salt and pepper; cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese; cook until cheese has melted.

title: all-purpose italian sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for approximately an hour. This will taste even better the next day.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie crust at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until golden.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Boil noodles and set aside.
Brown cabbage in butter in a skillet.
Pour this mixture over cooked noodles and serve hot.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, cucumber, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Separate egg yolks from egg whites.
Dice whites and add to potato mixture.
Sieve yolks and combine with sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar and mustard.
Add to potato mixture.
Mix carefully.
Chill several hours before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and shred, place in bowl.
Add soups and sour cream.
Mix well.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture, sprinkle on cheese, roll up and lay in pan (lined with chicken mixture). Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, for 40 minutes at 350 degrees. Uncover and bake 5-8 more minutes.
Can also substitute beef for chicken.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Stir corn syrup and sugar in saucepan over medium heat until sugar is melted and mixture boils; remove from heat.
Stir in butter until melted; set aside to cool slightly. Meanwhile, beat eggs, flour and vanilla in large bowl with a fork; add corn syrup mixture, beating constantly.
In pie shell, layer chocolate chips, coconut, then pecans.
Pour in filling mixture. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl until smooth and spreadable.

title: burritos
directions: Prepare tortillas according to package.
Cook onions in butter until translucent.
Add beans; cook and stir until heated through. Spoon 1/4 cup of mixture onto each tortilla near one edge.
Top with cheese and 1 tablespoon of taco sauce.
Fold nearest edge over to cover filling.
Fold in both sides, envelope fashion. Serve with taco sauce.
Makes 8 burritos.

title: green beans with water chestnuts
directions: Saute celery in butter in medium saucepan until tender.
Add flour, seasoned salt, pepper, soup and evaporated milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Drain chestnuts.
Place 1/2 of drained beans in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 chestnuts, pimiento, cheese and sauce.
Repeat with second layer.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle top with onions.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes longer.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients. Press firmly into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon crisp, remove from heat and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Cook onion and pepper in bacon drippings until onion is clear.
Add tomato juice, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and bacon; mix well.
Cover with a tight fitting lid and remove from heat.
Some people like their Spanish Rice dry, others prefer it juicy. Adjust the rice to suit your taste.

title: chocolate chip ice cream
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Pour into at least a 5-quart ice cream freezer.
Add all other ingredients except the chocolate chips. Stir well.
Freeze in freezer until almost finished and then add chips.
Let freezer run to mix chips well.
Pack with ice to firm well.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.

title: pudding cake dessert
directions: Take "skin" off top of cake to reveal cake.
Spread vanilla pudding over top of cake; let set for a few minutes to settle. Spread pie filling or pudding of your favorite flavor over vanilla pudding; let set a few minutes to settle.
Spread Cool Whip over filling or pudding.
Fix, then keep cool for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast and buttermilk to dry ingredients and stir with a fork until a soft dough is formed.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead briefly.
Store in tightly closed plastic bag in the refrigerator; use as needed.
Pat out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Do not let rise at any time.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 450° for 10 minutes.
Dough lasts a week and yields a dozen per day.

title: disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Smear the inside of an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan with shortening.
Melt butter over low heat.
In a bowl, stir the cocoa and sugar together, then stir in the melted butter.
Add the eggs and vanilla and stir again.
Add the flour and salt and mix until smooth.
(If you're adding nuts, now's the time.)
Scrape the mixture into greased pan and spread out into an even layer.
Bake in a 350° oven until the brownies just begin to pull away from the sides of the pan.
You can use the old toothpick method.
Takes about 40 to 50 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until golden brown. Serve warm.
Serves 15.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish and cover with topping.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: almond float
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1 cup of water.
Heat evaporated milk, 3 cups water and sugar to just below boiling point.
Add gelatine to hot mixture and stir until mixed.
Cool, then add extract.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until set.
Cut into cubes and serve mixed with desired fruits - fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges, lychee, peaches are suggested.

title: sausage 'n squash bake
directions: Halve and seed squash; place, cut side down, in buttered shallow baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and water. Add 1 cup chow mein noodles, tuna, celery, cashews, onion and pepper. Toss lightly.
Place in ungreased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle remaining noodles on top. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 15 minutes, usually longer, or until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with drained mandarin oranges.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Cover ground beef with water and cook.
Cook all ingredients until thick.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Mix together vegetable oil and potatoes in 9-inch pie plate. Press into pie crust shape. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until crust begins to brown.
Remove from oven.

title: guaranteed world class caesar salad recipe
directions: A large wooden bowl (unfinished) works best for making a Caesar Salad.
In the bowl, mash the peeled garlic cloves with a fork.
Add the anchovies and continue to mash together into a fine paste.
Using the back of a wooden salad spoon, mash the garlic and anchovies into the sides and bottom of the bowl.
Break the coddled egg into the bowl and blend lightly.
Add the lemon juice and balsamic vinegar and mix thoroughly with the previously mashed garlic, anchovies and egg.
Then add the olive oil and blend.
Mix in the Parmesan cheese last.
When ready to serve, add the lettuce and toss until the leaves are coated with the dressing.
Add the croutons last and toss lightly to mix.
Serve immediately on cold plates with a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese and cracked black pepper (preferably Indian telecherry pepper).

title: creoled stewed okra
directions: Soak the chickpeas for five to six hours.
Pressure cook them with a little water until they are done.
Cool the chickpeas and drain them thoroughly.
Blend the chickpeas in a mixer to a puree. Add crushed garlic, coriander leaves, chopped onion, lemon juice and salt.
Mix well.
Keep the chickpeas mixture in the refrigerator for an hour or so.
Divide and roll the mixture into patties.
Heat oil and shallow fry the chickpea patties until they are done.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: dixie house baked squash
directions: Rinse and
trim ends of squash.
Cut squash into 2-inch pieces.
Place
in
boiling, salted water to cover.
Cook just until tender,
about
minutes.
Drain in colander, mash to remove remaining
liquid.
Drain for 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
If
using
fresh onions, saute in butter until soft, about 5
minutes.
Combine drained squash, onions, butter, 1/2 cup dry bread crumbs, sugar, salt, eggs and pepper.
Pour into lightly greased
1/2-quart
casserole
dish
and
top
with remaining 1/2
cup bread crumbs.
Bake, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes
or until set.
Remove cover and return to oven.
Bake until bread crumbs are golden, about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: candied sauerkraut
directions: Spread kraut in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion, celery seed, garlic powder, sugar and bacon.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Bake 3 hours at 325° (if it gets too dry, add more tomatoes).
Dish should be moist, but not runny, when served.
Do not cover while baking.

title: irish potato candy(no potatoes in this)
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter or margarine and cream cheese. Blend well.
Beat in vanilla and confectioners sugar, then mix in coconut.
Form into walnut size balls.
Roll in cinnamon; refrigerate until firm.
Do not use light cream cheese.

title: better than sex cake(well ... decide for yourself)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook and drain green beans (do not overcook).
In a 1-quart casserole, blend soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper until smooth. Stir in beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts. Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely.

title: miracle fudge frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler over simmering water.
When smooth, remove from heat.
Cool, stirring frequently until spreading consistency.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cut deboned chicken up into bite size pieces; crumble cornbread.
Mix chicken and cornbread with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Moist and delicious.

title: peanut butter snowballs
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar, peanut butter and butter. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet. Chill for 30 minutes or until firm.
Meanwhile, melt the almond bark in a double boiler.
Dip balls in almond bark, place on waxed paper to harden.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.
Cool and eat!

title: peanut butter and special k treats
directions: Mix sugar and Karo and heat over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Pour over Special K; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper or foil.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch dish and line with whole graham crackers. Mix instant pudding with milk; beat two minutes, then fold in all the Cool Whip.
Pour a good layer over graham crackers.
Add another layer of crackers, then another of pudding.
Top with a layer of crackers.
Frost with Fudge Icing and let stand in the refrigerator all day or overnight before serving.

title: oven glazed chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange chicken.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until done.
Cooking Time:
1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread, milk, oil, eggs, corn, baking powder, and salt together.
Brown hambuger meat and drain.
Pour half the batter into greased pan.
Then add grated cheese and peppers over mixture.
Then pour the remaining batter on top.
Bake for about 1 hour, in 350° oven.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Make paste of vinegar, sugar, flour and salt; add water. Blend and pour over other ingredients.
Cook slowly for 1 hour. If desired, place wieners on top last 20 minutes.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Arrange Twinkies on a plate.
Top with whipped cream.
Chop Snickers bar and sprinkle over Twinkies; then top with M&M's.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat.
Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Mix with cheese mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill and cut in squares.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: creamy garlic mushrooms(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: In bowl, mix mayo, salt, pepper, garlic and cream.
Take mushrooms and add dill, then fold into dressing mixture.
Line serving dish with lettuce and serve.
Garnish with fresh dill.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Bring fruit juice and sugar to a boil.
Mix flour, oil and water to form dough for dumplings.
Drop dumplings by the spoonful into boiling juice.
Cook until done.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mix together and spread on small rye bread slices.
Put thin slices of cucumber on top.
Shake on some dill weed.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind up all ingredients in meat grinder or food processor, except crushed pineapple.
Put in large bowl.
Add the crushed pineapple.
Stir.
Add sugar to taste.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Boil water. Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved. Add cranberry sauce, then add thawed strawberries. Chill and serve.

title: beef sausage rolls
directions: Spread rolls in an ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with hash browns and uncooked sausage.
Cover with cheese, onion, green and red peppers, salt and pepper.
Pour eggs over all and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in an oblong pan.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into balls about the size of walnuts.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or more.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
They may be frozen before baking.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: congealed spiced peach salad
directions: Drain peaches, saving 1 cup syrup.
Chop peaches coarsely. Bring syrup, vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain syrup and discard cloves.
Dissolve gelatin in hot syrup.
Add cold water and peaches.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Pour into mold or 9 x 9-inch dish.

title: tabouli
directions: *There are many different varieties of beans (brown, white, red speckled, stripped or you name it!) in Africa because beans are the protein substitute in the place of meats.
You could substitute any dried bean.

title: cheddar pecan spread
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill in covered container. Use as sandwich spread or on crackers.

title: frozen peanut butter and jelly pie
directions: Note:
Sugar-free pudding, skim milk, light jam and light topping may be used.

title: pie crust
directions: In a mixing bowl, cut shortening into flour and salt, using a pastry blender or two knives, until consistency of small peas. Blend in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, tossing with a fork. Gather dough into a bowl.

title: easy cabbage dinner
directions: Place first three ingredients in crock-pot and cover with water.
Salt and pepper as needed.
Let cook several hours on low heat.
Cut sausage into pieces and add to mixture 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil; remove.
Saute onions, garlic, peppers and mushrooms 5 to 10 minutes.
Add chicken and tomatoes.
Simmer 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Add wine.
Simmer another 1/2 to 3/4 hour, uncovered.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: oatmeal apple bars
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add oats, brown sugar and butter.
Mix with pastry blender until grainy.
Put half of mixture into lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Cover mixture with apples.
Mix nuts and granulated sugar.
Sprinkle half on apples and dot with butter.
Put on remaining mix and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in slow oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cut while still warm.

title: tuscan pork roast
directions: Garnishes: fresh herbs and roasted garlic.
Process first 8 ingredients in a food processor or blender 2 minutes or until smooth, stopping cone to scrape down sides; set pesto mixture aside.
Open butterflied roast, and place between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; flatten to 1/2- inch thickness, using a mallet or rolling pin.
Spread about two-thirds pesto mixture over roast.
Roll up jellyroll fashion, starting with long side, and secure at 2-inch intervals, using heavy string.
Place roast in a shallow roasting pan; cover with remaining pesto mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 1 hour or until a meat thermometer inserted into thickest portion registers 160°.
Remove from the pan, reserving drippings in pan; keep roast warm.

title: zucchini bread plus
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg in large bowl.
Beat eggs in mixer bowl until thick and lemon colored.
Add oil; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix just until moistened.
Stir in zucchini, apricots, apple, pineapple, raisins, coconut and nuts.
Spoon into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Remove to wire rack to cool.
Can be baked in Bundt pan.

title: mock mayonnaise
directions: Beat all ingredients with hand beater until smooth.
Cover dressing.
Refrigerate at least two hours.
Makes about one cup dressing.

title: "bit's" country style lemonade
directions: Squeeze and cut up lemons.
Add sugar and press sugar and lemons together.
Add water to taste.
Serve with ice.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Stir in nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Put cucumbers, onions and green peppers through a food chopper, using a medium blade.
In a 5 or 6-quart saucepan, combine vegetables, celery seed, mustard seed, salt, cloves, turmeric, vinegar and sugar.
Quickly bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 3 hours, or until reduced to about 5 pints.
Put into pint jars and seal.
Process for about 15 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes 5 pints.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and mayonnaise together in a large bowl.
Blend in chicken, celery, onion and water chestnuts.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Mix stuffing with melted butter and sprinkle mixture on top of the chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly and browned on top.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Slice butter thin, then mix all together.

title: egg rolls
directions: Saute vegetables in oil seasoned with salt, pepper and sugar. Set aside.
Saute meat seasoned with soy sauce and garlic powder. Set aside.
Add to vegetable mixture and drain liquid.
Place 1 egg roll skin with a corner toward you.
Put a big tablespoon of filling on center of skin.
Fold bottom corner up over filling. Overlap 2 opposite side corners.
Moisten top corner with water; fold over to form roll.
Repeat.
Heat oil for deep fry until 375°. Fry egg rolls until golden brown.
Serve with Sweet and Sour Sauce.

title: cauliflower pea salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into flowerets.
Chop celery and green onions. Thaw peas and mix together.
Prepare dressing mix and toss it all together.
Chill before serving.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until center is done.
Test with knife or toothpick; must come out clean without mixture on them, 30 to 45 minutes.
Will vary with size and shape of pan used.
Top will be springy.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Alternately spear steak, tomatoes, mushrooms, squash, onion halves and pepper pieces on four 8-inch bamboo skewers (not metal); place on Microwave Plus 11 1/2 x 12-inch bacon/roasting rack. Slather kabobs with barbecue sauce. Broil 3 to 4 minutes, turning once to brown. Baste again; microcook on Medium (50%) 1 minute; check for doneness.
Continue basting and cooking in 1-minute intervals until done. Makes 2 servings, two 8-inch kabobs each. Serve with cooked riso or orzo pasta, tossed with butter and chopped, fresh parsley.

title: coconut pie 2
directions: Melt margarine.
Add to all remaining ingredients that have been covered in a mixing bowl.
Cover bowl and store in refrigerator overnight.
Cook in a deep dish pie shell at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: To prepare eggplant, place in a baking pan and prick top in 4 or 5 places with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until skin is wrinkled and the surface is soft.
Cool eggplant slightly and cut in half.
Scoop out the flesh and place in a blender.
Add onion, garlic, parsley and mint; blend until well mixed.
Combine olive oil, vinegar and lemon juice; add to thin eggplant mixture and blend well.
Season with salt and pepper. Chill served with toasted French or pita bread.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together well.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer.
Finish filling freezer with milk.
Freeze as usual.

title: chocolate pan pie
directions: Melt oleo in bottom of cake pan.
Add nuts and flour.
Mix and pat in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (until light brown).
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and half of the Cool Whip.
Spread on crust and chill.
Mix together puddings and 3 cups milk.
Let stand 20 minutes, then spread on top of layers. Top with the rest of the Cool Whip and garnish with walnut halves and candied cherries.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush 3/4 of the oreos into a 13 x 9 inch dish, pressing firmly down.
In a separate bowl, beat milk, vanilla, sugar and cream cheese until creamy.
Add instant pudding.
Mix again until creamy and pour over cookies.
Cover with whipped topping and sprinkle remaining oreos on top.

title: veggie pizza(appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out crescent rolls in flat sheet and bake 8 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool.
Mix dressing mix, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread on cool crust.
Sprinkle vegetables in order over top, using wax paper to press each layer down.
Sprinkle cheeses over top.
Cut and serve.
Best when frozen.

title: hello dolly cookies(7 layer)
directions: Melt the margarine or butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: garlic oil
directions: Combine oil and garlic in a covered container.
Store in cupboard 2 to 3 days.
Shake occasionally.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, puddings and water in saucepan; cook mixture over medium heat until it starts to boil.
Let mixture cool. Blend in remaining ingredients and refrigerate until set.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the margarine, sour cream and egg together. Add the whole kernel corn, cream-style corn and muffin mix. Bake 1 hour in a glass casserole at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cod and tater bake
directions: Arrange fish in lightly greased baking dish.
Cover with sauce made of soup, etc.
Place potatoes on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until hot through at 350°.

title: brownies a la k. hepburn
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Remove from heat. Stir in sugar. Add eggs and vanilla and beat like mad!
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put 1/2 of batter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 of cinnamon sugar mixture.
Top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle on the rest of the sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marie ritcher's meringue
directions: Combine cornstarch and cold water.
Stir in boiling water and cook until clear; cool.
Whip egg whites with salt until fluffy. Using low setting, beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Pour cooled cornstarch mixture over egg whites and beat until light and fluffy.
Pile high on pie (spreading to the edge of pie crust). Brown lightly at 350° for 15 minutes or until light tan.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Crimp edges of pastry shell.
Mix together molasses, boiling water and baking soda.
Pour in well-beaten egg; set aside.
Mix flour with sugar, salt and cinnamon; chop in shortening to form crumbs.
Pour molasses mixture into pastry shell.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Cool.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Pour together condensed milk and lemon concentrate.
Whisk until thickened.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Pour into crust.
Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb and stir very well.
Add sugar, crushed pineapple, juice and nuts.
Mix well and pour into a mold or shallow pan which has been rubbed with salad dressing.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to use.
This salad will keep for several days.

title: donut sundae
directions: Place donut in a small serving bowl.
Put a scoop of ice cream in the middle of the donut.
Next, pour a little chocolate sauce on top and sprinkle with some nuts.

title: green pepper saute
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion, pepper and garlic in hot oil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Cover and steam over low heat for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with oregano, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook a few minutes longer until tender.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add corn and stewed tomatoes; remove from fire.
Cook noodles; rinse and add to ground beef mixture.
Set oven at 350°. Put in oven for 30 minutes.
Add cheese and leave in oven until melted.

title: cheesy enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Mix hamburger meat, refried beans, cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup together in a large bowl.
Place 2 to 4 shells on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Add half of the mixture.
Place slices of cheese all over.
Place 2 to 4 shells on top of cheese.
Add rest of mixture on top of shells.
Place slices of cheese on top. Bake at 425° until cheese is melted.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together and spread on top of the cake.
Place the cake in the oven and put on broil until it is browned lightly.
This cake freezes well.

title: krista's snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, beat together butter, brown sugar and 3/4 cup granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
In medium bowl, combine flour, oats, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet.
In small bowl, combine remaining 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle lightly over each cookie.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire cooling rack.
Makes 54 servings.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread sauerkraut on bottom; add tomato slices; dot with butter.
Pour over Thousand Island dressing.
Cover with corned beef.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Separate rolls and place on top of casserole.
Sprinkle crackers and caraway seed on top.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Check after 15 minutes to see if rolls are browned.)

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients with apples.
Make a well in middle of mixture. Pour in oil and well beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Stir and pour in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Walnuts or pecans can be added to batter.

title: hamburger and rice
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Dice green pepper and add to hamburger.
Cook rice according to directions, then mix with hamburger and pepper.
Mix in soy sauce and eat!

title: chicken bracciole
directions: Combine last 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle combination on each chicken breast.
Place 1 slice Provolone cheese on each chicken breast.
Roll and tie with string.
Place in shallow pan and simmer in tomato sauce or place in small amount of butter on each and bake.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oyster stuffed squash
directions: Place squash cut sides down into 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover; bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; turn squash over. Saute onion, celery and oysters until tender; add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, French dressing and soft bread, 1/2 cup in each squash.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Bring all ingredients (except mushrooms) to a boil.
Add mushrooms and simmer 6 minutes.
Chill several hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve.
Best prepared day before.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: For cocoa mix, stir together milk powder, nondairy creamer, cocoa powder, Equal and, if desired, cinnamon.
Cover and store in an airtight container.

title: russian sauerkraut bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk, water, yeast and honey.
Stir vigorously.
Let bowl stand in a warm place 5 to 10 minutes or until yeast foams.
Stir in enough whole wheat flour to make a thick batter.
Cover bowl with a towel and let rise in a warm place 30 minutes.
Add the white flour, a little at a time, until a stiff dough forms.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Cook until zucchini is done.
Add cheese the last 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; save broth.
Take 2/3 cup corn bread stuffing and place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Debone chicken and lay over stuffing.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain well.
Saute onion in oil. Add undiluted soup and Worcestershire.
Mix with spinach and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Heat in a 325° oven until hot through.
Serves 10.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and pimentos and drain well. Place in large bowl.
Combine sugar, oil, vinegar, pepper and salt; pour over beans.
Mix well and place in refrigerator dish with a tight fitting cover.
Keep cold until ready to serve. Flavor improves after 3 or 4 days.

title: pineapple nut spice cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and egg whites.
Beat well and then add nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven; set oven at 325° and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: fish dijon
directions: Place fillets on a nonstick baking dish.
Sprinkle lemon juice over the top.
Bake covered at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
While fish bakes, melt margarine in a small saucepan.
Blend in cornstarch and pepper until smooth.
Add milk. Heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until hot, then spoon sauce over baked fish fillets.
Serve immediately on warmed platter.
Yield:
4 servings.
Calories per serving:

title: home-canned pork and beans
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Boil in same water for 45 minutes.
Drain beans, reserving liquid.
Add all ingredients to beans and 2 cups bean liquid.
Mix well.
Pack in clean jars to within 1-inch of top. Put on cap and screw firmly tight.
Process pints and quarts 60 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
Yields 8 pints.

title: chicken casserole *
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from the bones and strain broth, saving all the broth.
Cook noodles in broth, reserving one cup of broth.
Set aside.
Brown green pepper, onion, clove of garlic, pimentos, mushrooms and olives in the margarine.
Drain noodles.
Add noodles, reserve broth, cheese, chicken, salt and pepper to browned ingredients.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour in casserole.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Serves 10 to 12.
Better if made a day ahead and refrigerated overnight before cooking.
Freezes well.

title: baked rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour in a covered dish at 350°.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oleo until crumbly.
Take 1 cup of mixture and save for topping.
Into the rest of batter, add egg. Pat into pan and put up around sides of pan.
Mix crushed pineapple and pie filling; put over crumb mixture.
Sprinkle top with the rest of crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil; blend.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.
Add carrots, nuts and coconut. Grease and flour cake pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon raisin bread
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and the yeast.
Heat milk, water, 1/4 cup sugar, oil and salt over low heat until warm.
Add liquid ingredients to flour-yeast mixture and beat with electric mixer until smooth (about 3 minutes).
Blend in egg; stir in raisins. Stir in enough remaining flour to make moderately soft dough.
On lightly floured surface, knead until smooth and satiny, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Cover dough with a bowl and let rest 20 minutes. Combine 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half to a 7 x 4-inch rectangle.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with 1/2 the cinnamon-sugar mixture. Beginning at narrow side, roll up tightly, pressing dough into roll at each turn. Press ends to seal and fold under loaf.
Place in two greased loaf pans; brush tops with melted butter.
Let rise in warm place until double, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. When done, remove from pans immediately and cool on wire rack. If you like, brush tops with butter again.
Cool completely before storing.

title: 5-quart homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all together, then pour into the freezer; fill freezer 1/2 up with milk.
Stir to mix.
Plug in until firm.

title: cheesy potato beef casserole
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, cook beef until no longer pink; drain. Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with mushrooms. Combine potatoes and contents of sauce mix packets, water, milk, butter, salts and pepper. Pour over beef and mushrooms. Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and cream together.
Add Wesson oil and mix.
Sift all dry ingredients together and mix with eggs and sugar.
Add the chopped dates and nuts; last of all add the grated carrots.
Mix well together.
Pour batter into a greased angel food cake pan and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Let cool in pan upside down.
Cake can be served with or without your favorite frosting.
You may also use whipped cream or a vanilla sauce instead of frosting.

title: rice salad dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill until ready to serve.

title: quick ham quiche
directions: Sprinkle ham, cheese and onion in a greased 9-inch pie pan. Blend remaining ingredients in blender or food processor.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chili egg puff
directions: Beat eggs until light brown and lemon colored.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, Jack cheese and melted butter, blending smoothly.
Stir in chili.
Pour mixture into well-buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes until top is light brown and center firm.

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes, sour cream and parsley in a skillet.
Add potatoes and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes, or until done.
Let stand 30 minutes. Blend sour cream and parsley in a bowl.
Toss with potato mixture. Great served with grilled knockwurst.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and eggs and beat.
Grate lemon rind and add to the mixture.
Blend in buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool for ten.
Mix 1 cup confectioners sugar and enough juice from lemon to make a glaze.

title: ambrosia cake dessert
directions: Prepare cake as directed and bake.
Chill cake.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Prepare jello; place bowl in ice water to chill.
Split cake in half to make 2 layers.
Place bottom half of cake in pan; cover with half pudding.
Top with top part of cake and remaining pudding.
Spoon gelatin over bananas as soon as it reaches a thick, syrupy stage.
Chill until jello is firm.

title: uncle ken's fudge cookies
directions: Mix milk, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Cook 2 minutes after it boils on low heat.
After this boils, take off burner and add peanut butter and mix together.
Mix oatmeal and cocoa together and add.
Stir together well and drop on waxed paper. Let cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend. Chill. Serve with any sliced fruit.

title: phesant farms honey onions
directions: Bring
onions to boil in salted water.	Cook 5 minutes; pour off water.	Add chili sauce and honey.
Simmer slowly in butter for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking pan.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper. Vary amount according to your taste.
Put tin foil over pan.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: dirt cake
directions: Chop up cookies. Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Mix cream cheese and butter. Leave no lumps. Then mix both mixtures together. In bowl, put layer of cookies. Pour mixture on top. Put remaining cookies on top. Keep in the fridge.

title: fresh corn soup
directions: Cook potatoes and ham or bacon in chicken broth until potatoes are soft.
Add corn and sugar; cook about 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: romaine-vegetable salad
directions: Dressing:
Mix vinegar, oil, soy sauce and five-spice powder in a custard cup or small bowl; set aside.

title: zucchini florentine
directions: Steam zucchini in water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir to even cooking.
Drain.
Layer zucchini and onions in 2-quart casserole or baking dish.

title: sour cream pie(not finished)
directions: Soak the raisins in hot water to soften, then pour off the water.
Mix all other ingredients, except raisins and cinnamon. Add the raisins and cinnamon.
Put in double crust pie shells. Bake at 350° until golden brown and the pie is done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit and juices together.
Stir in sliced bananas and strawberries.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix and mix thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 18-inch cake pan.
Spread pecans on bottom and then coconut.
Mix cake according to directions on box and pour into pan.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Skin and wash chicken breasts.
Cut into serving pieces.
Mix garlic, salt, pepper and flour; coat chicken.
Then brown in oil. Add other ingredients.
Cook until tender.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Add to chicken.
Cook a little longer.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit (very well) in colander, reserving juices. Combine juices and measure 3 cups into a saucepan.
Add pudding mix, sugar and tapioca.
Bring to boil stirring constantly. Simmer until mixture begins to thicken.
Cool to room temperature and pour over drained fruit.
Add nuts and coconut if desired and maraschino cherries for color.
Refrigerate well before serving.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in butter Crisco.
Add veggies, garlic and paprika.
Add tomatoes and soy sauce.
Cook until meat is tender. Mix water with cornstarch and add to mixture.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Blend rice, sugar and milk.
Cook in double boiler. When rice is tender, take out some hot milk and let cool slightly, then add beaten eggs and return to the rest of the mixture. Continue cooking until it thickens slightly.
Lastly add vanilla and cinnamon.

title: hearty tuna casserole
directions: Note:
You may substitute canned drained salmon for tuna.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Mix all together well and shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and flatten with a glass. Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.
Don't overbake.

title: hot dog soup
directions: Saute and brown with small amount of butter the onion and hot dogs.
Drain potatoes and mix all ingredients.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: On
medium
heat,
in
a medium saucepan, add broccoli, onion and margarine until broccoli is thawed.
Add Cheez Whiz, uncooked Minute
rice and cream of mushroom soup to saucepan. Stir
all ingredients
together until Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup
are completely	liquefied
or
melted.	Spray
nonstick cooking spray into
a
quart casserole dish, then add casserole contents.
Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for approximately 5 minutes before serving.

title: egg and mushroom quiche
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add finely chopped mushrooms.
Cook just until limp and juices are released.
Add cracker crumbs to mushroom mixture and stir together until well blended.
Line bottom and side of a nice size pie pan with this mixture forming a crust.
Slice green onions in small round pieces and lay on top of crust.
Add shredded Monterey Jack cheese on top of onions.
Next, you take your cottage cheese and 3 eggs and put them in a blender and blend just until nicely blended.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour carefully over cheese.
Sprinkle the top with paprika.
Bake in medium oven on 350° for 30 minutes.

title: faye's deviled chicken
directions: Salt chicken. Mix mayonnaise, margarine and mustard. Dip chicken pieces in mayonnaise mixture, then roll in stuffing crumbs. Place in baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or less. (Do not overcook.)

title: orange crush ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze.

title: herbed lentils and rice
directions: Mix all, leaving 2 ounces of cheese to put on top.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring every 1/2 hour.
Top with remaining cheese and return to oven to melt.
Serves 6.

title: rice salad
directions: Stir all of the ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight. Stir the mixture before serving.

title: melon rings with strawberries
directions: Rinse strawberries, but do not hull.
Set aside to drain.
Cut melon crosswise into 1-inch thick rings.
Remove seeds.
Place slices on individual plates.
With a knife, carefully cut around the slice 1/4 inch from the rind; do not remove rind.
Slice pulp to make bite size pieces, leaving rind intact.
Arrange five or six strawberries in the center of each melon slice.
Makes 5 servings.

title: tom selleck cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan as directed on package.
While cake is still hot, poke holes in top of cake with wooden spoon and pour 1 can Eagle Brand milk over top.
Let cool and put Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with butter brickle pieces or crushed up Heath bar.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: salmonburgers
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet.
Add onion and cook over medium heat until tender.
Remove from heat and put in mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup potato chips, egg, salt and salmon.
Mix well. Shape into six patties.
Coat with remaining potato chips.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add patties; fry on one side until golden brown. Turn and fry other side until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel. Serve on toasted hamburger buns.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook until rice is done, then add milk.
Serve hot.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add shallots, mushrooms, thyme and chicken breasts. Sprinkle parsley and nutmeg over chicken.
Add wine and lemon juice; simmer, covered, for about 10 minutes.
Remove chicken to serving dish.
Add prawns to broth; cook about 1 minute, or until done.
Remove prawns to serving dish.

title: sausage tartlets
directions: Prepare pie crust mix; press in mini muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: baked pineapple(excellent side dish with ham)
directions: Drain the pineapple, saving the juice.
Mix the pineapple with the grated cheese.
Mix the flour and sugar in saucepan.
Add the juice from the drained pineapple and the vanilla.
Heat just to blend well.
Put the pineapple-cheese mixture in an 8-inch square baking dish and cover with the sauce.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and Crisco.
Set aside 1/2 cup for topping.
Combine molasses, water, egg and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°, then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Drain artichokes and save marinade.
Saute onion and garlic in part of the marinade for about 5 minutes.
Beat eggs and add all other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cut into 1-inch squares, serve hot.
May be cooked in smaller container for thicker slices.
Serve as a vegetable, side dish or appetizer.

title: busy day pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Put meat in a heavy Dutch oven.
Mix remaining ingredients in a small bowl; spread over top and sides of roast.
Cover and bake about 3 hours or until tender.
Lift meat to cutting board.
Let stand about 5 minutes; then cut in thin slices.
Pour gravy into a sauce boat to spoon over each serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in 5 c. water until tender.
Do not drain potatoes. Add remaining ingredients and cook until cheese is melted.
Stir occasionally.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In skillet brown hamburger and onion.
In separate skillet melt together butter and flour.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Cut up cheese in this mixture and cook until melted.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms together.
Cook 1/2 package spaghetti according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle more cheese on top before baking.
Very good warmed over.

title: night before french toast
directions: Place bread slices in 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar, salt and vanilla; pour over bread.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours.
Remove from refrigerator.
Uncover and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve as a salad or spread on bread as sandwiches.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Pour kraut in a saucepan and add sugar.
Let come to a boil. Add onion, celery, green pepper and pimentos.
Let come to a boil again.
Cool in refrigerator.
This will last from 1 to 2 weeks.

title: brunch-breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain the sausage.
Place sausage in a large bowl. Add eggs, soup, hash browns, mayonnaise and mushrooms.
Mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 350° until done.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese and place back in oven until melted.
Cut in squares and serve.
This freezes well.

title: biscuits (plain)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening; add milk to make soft dough.
Knead lightly; roll 1/4-inch thick, cut and bake in a 425° to 450° oven about 8 to 12 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar, cinnamon and shortening.
Blend until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture for topping.
To remaining crumbs add baking powder and soda, then add milk and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in two square cake pans.
Cover with the dry crumbs and sprinkle more cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until toothpick comes out clean at center.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugars gradually.
Add egg; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture and mix well.
Form balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork and bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: lady baltimore frosting and cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and mix as any other cake.
I use 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks and save the 3 whites for frosting.
Make three layers.

title: jello fruit pie
directions: Blend water, sugar and cornstarch. Cook until thick and clear. Add jello.
Let cool.
Pour over strained fruit (if in can) in pie shell.
Add Cool Whip, if desired.

title: country fried chicken breading
directions: Dip chicken in milk mixture, then in seasoning and flour mixture.
Deep fat fry for 18 minutes, or until nicely browned.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix the milk, apple juice concentrate, egg whites and oil in bowl or blender.
Add to dry ingredients and mix.
Add chopped apples, nuts and raisins.

title: diabetic pork chop noodle casserole(calories: 287)
directions: Place the cooked noodles in a small individual casserole.
Add grated onion, salt, pepper and sage to tomato juice.
Pour the tomato juice mixture over the noodles.
Place the browned pork chop on the noodles.
Cover the casserole and bake in a moderate oven for about 1/2 hour.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream 1/4 pound butter and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to butter mix, alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla.

title: "philly" fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Arrange cookie slices, slightly overlapping, on aluminum foil covered 14-inch pizza pan. Press edges to seal.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Remove from foil onto serving plate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Dip chicken pieces in Italian dressing and place on top of rice.
Pour rest of dressing over chicken.
Bake (covered with foil) in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: spanish olive cheese ball
directions: In an electric mixer bowl, beat at medium speed the cheese spreads and cream cheese with chives.
Add garlic powder and stuffed olives until smooth.
Stir in walnuts.
Cover and chill several hours.
Shape into a ball.
Garnish with pimiento-stuffed olive slices, parsley sprigs and pimiento strips, if desired. Cover and chill until serving time.
Serve with crackers.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef, breaking into small pieces.
Drain off fat. Add tomato juice, taco sauce and salt, pepper and garlic powder to your taste.
Sauce should be a little hotter to your taste than you would like it if you were eating it alone.
Add more taco sauce, if necessary.
Simmer so mixture thickens a little.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Cook vegetables as directed and drain.
Pour vegetables in casserole and mix in the can of soup. Put whole slices of cheese on top.
Shred the bread (without crusts) on top.
Melt the butter and drizzle over top.
Bake in moderate oven 350-375 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Can add 1 teaspoon coconut or lemon flavoring.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated; empty into a shallow baking dish.
Bake, stirring occasionally for 40 minutes or until tender and brown. Garnish with chopped fresh parsley.

title: mint tea punch
directions: Boil water, tea and mint for five minutes.
Remove mint; squeeze tea bags before removing from water.
Add sugar, lemon and pineapple juices.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serve over ice with a mint sprig in each glass.
Makes 3-1/2 quarts.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together and shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Cook over medium heat until done.

title: egg casserole
directions: Put croutons in bottom of greased 10 x 6 x 3-inch pan. Sprinkle cheese over croutons.
Beat other ingredients and pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: rhonda's special punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients except 7-Up.
Freeze, then remove 1 hour before party. Before serving, pour 7-Up over punch.
Makes a slush.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and beat.
Add nuts last. Pour into a greased and floured large cookie sheet (11 x 15-inch).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Tear lettuce.
Mix all together. Let set for several hours.
Mix with Western dressing and Doritos when ready to eat.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix together butter, evaporated milk and cake mix.
Spread half of mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix together.
(Note: This burns easily, even in microwave.) Pour chocolate chips and pecans over hot bottom layer and spread caramel mixture on top. Put remaining cake mixture on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown beef in olive oil and drain.
Bring to simmer V-8 and tomato juice.
Add chopped onion, pepper, celery, mushrooms and garlic.
Add browned beef and tomato paste.
Sprinkle beef with fresh olive oil before adding to vegetable mixture.
Season with Italian dressing to taste.
Cook vermicelli with a little cooking oil.
Serve sauce over noodles.

title: danish coffee cake
directions: Mix well the first three ingredients as in pie dough.
Form into ball, divide in half and spread each ball on ungreased cookie sheet, 12 x 3 each.
Put 1/2 cup oleo and 1 cup water in pan; bring to boil until oleo is melted.
Remove from heat; add flour and extract all at once.
Stir quickly until all is smooth and leaves sides of pan.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until mixture is smooth and glossy.
Spread mixture over each piece of pastry. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham loaf
directions: Add first six ingredients together, mixing well.
Make into a loaf.
Put vinegar, catsup, mustard and brown sugar in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Pour over loaf and baste occasionally.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: irish american stew
directions: Brown meat slowly in bacon drippings over medium heat.
(Do not flour.)
Place meat in crock-pot and add remaining ingredients.
Cook overnight.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Trim crusts from as many slices of thin white bread as you wish to fix.
Cut each slice into 7 strips.
Bake in a 250° oven until crisp.
Thin the peanut butter with the oil.
Dip strips into peanut butter mixture until completely covered.
Roll in toasted bread crumbs, made from bread crusts.
Store in airtight container until ready to use.

title: fried corn
directions: Take a sharp knife and cut the tip edge off of corn; then scrape the ears.
Add butter in a skillet; pour corn into skillet and stir often.
Let cook 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Melt cheese and butter in top of double boiler.
Add soup and stir well. Add chopped broccoli and heat until broccoli has thawed.
Stir in drained mushrooms.
Serve warm.

title: perfection salad
directions: Stir jello into cold water, then add to hot water; stir very well.
Add dressing.
Chill until very syrupy, then add vegetables.
Pour into 1 quart or individual molds.
Unmold onto bed of greens.

title: johnny's mac and cheese
directions: Heat milk on medium in pot.
Cut cheese into small pieces. Stir until melts.
Add Parmesan cheese and salt.
Add hot and drained macaroni to sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream and Cool Whip together.
Next, add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill 1 hour, then top with fruit filling.

title: onion rose
directions: Any dark honey mustard or Ranch Style dressing.
Peel onion, leaving root end intact.
Cut onion vertically into quarters, cutting to within 1/2-inch of root end.
Cut each quarter into thirds.
Place onion in boiling water for 1 minute.
Remove and place in ice water for 5 minutes.
Loosen petals if necessary. Drain onion cut side down.
Place flour in a Ziploc bag.
Add onion, shaking to coat.
Dip onion in egg.
Place cracker crumbs in plastic bag.
Add onion, tossing to coat.
Chill 1 hour.
Pour oil to depth of 3 inches into fryer and heat to 375°.
Fry onion 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown; drain on paper towel.
Salt if necessary.
Serve with dressings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over heat for about 30 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Put lettuce and green onions in a large salad bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add vinegar and sugar to drippings.
Bring to boil and pour over lettuce.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Serves 4.

title: caramel mocha sundae
directions: Mix coffee and brown sugar in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Continue cooking until mixture begins to thicken and become syrupy, 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat. Mix in vanilla and brandy.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour syrup over ice cream.
Dollop or pipe whipped cream over and pour remaining syrup over.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, bread, tomato juice, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Stir in ground beef.

title: delicious potatoes
directions: Filling in a casserole dish, slice potatoes and 1 onion. Sprinkle with salts and add margarine if desired.
Mix well and add 3/4 cup water.
Cook in microwave on High for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: strawberry cream delight
directions: Mix the following with mixer:
cream cheese and condensed milk. Fold into cream cheese mixture the whipping cream.
Layer 1/2 cake, 1/2 strawberries and 1/2 cream mixture.
Repeat layers.
Chill overnight.
Good with fresh peaches in the summer.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking soda and mix well.
Add bananas and walnuts and mix again. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool for 10 minutes and turn out of pan.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Boil together for three hours, stirring occasionally.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a large, heavy bottom pan, saute the chopped onions in the oil on medium-high heat until golden brown (about 7 to 10 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients (not the beer!); bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; let simmer, uncovered, for 4 hours.
Every 30 minutes or after each beer, whichever comes first, stir to prevent sticking.
After the first 2 1/2 hours of simmering, taste periodically (let it cool first, though).
Follow with a swallow of cold beer.
Puree in a blender or food processor in small batches.*
Pour the sauce into another container.
A clean 1-gallon plastic milk jug works quite well.

title: artichokes in wine sauce
directions: Prepare artichokes by cutting off the tips of the leaves and stems.
Spread open and remove inner small leaves and thistles. Place side by side, upright, in a small saucepan; keep upright while cooking.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring to rolling boil and pour over filled jars; seal.
If you like, you can give the jars a hot bath.
Sometimes it will make the jars seal better.

title: velvety custard pie
directions: Heat scalded milk on stove until scum forms on milk. Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk at once.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Dash with nutmeg.

title: fresh vegetables with creamy garlic sauce
directions: In a small bowl, combine yogurt, garlic and olive oil. Arrange remaining ingredients on a large platter.
Mound yogurt sauce in the center.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 4.

title: unreal potato salad
directions: Crumble crackers.
Chop eggs, celery, green pepper, pickles, olives, onion and radishes.
Add dry mustard and crumbled crackers.
Mix thoroughly.
Add mayonnaise and mix again. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Chop apples into small pieces.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vinegar.
Drain pineapple and add to mixture.
Chop peanuts and add to mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: cheesy meaty macaroni casserole
directions: *If a dairy restricted diet is a necessity, use either the non-fat Mozzarella or use Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let
cream cheese soften.
Mix cream cheese and Cheddar cheese together.
Add
onions,
sauce and salt to cheese mixture.
Roll into a ball.
Roll ball in pecans.
Put in refrigerator.

title: russian-style fried potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender in boiling salted water to cover. Drain potatoes; let cool.
Peel potatoes, and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat oil in heavy skillet; add potatoes, onions and garlic.
