Season to taste; fry until golden brown, turning to brown on all sides.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine sugar, water, cream of tartar and salt in saucepan. Bring to boil; stir until sugar dissolves.
Very slowly add to unbeaten egg whites in bowl, beating constantly with mixer until stiff peaks form.
Beat in vanilla.
This will frost 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers or 1 (10-inch) tube cake.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, 1 1/3 cups of instant potatoes (dry), egg, salt, pepper, onion, catsup and milk.
Spread in ungreased pie pan.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes.
Prepare remaining potatoes as directed on package for 4 servings.
Top baked meat loaf with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: peach delight
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
Stir in 1/2 of the Dream Whip and all the peaches.
Break cake into bite size pieces and mix well with jello mixture.
Press into pan and place in refrigerator. When mixture firms, top with remaining Dream Whip.
May use peach slices and/or cherries to garnish.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream the Crisco and add sugar gradually while creaming.
Add the beaten eggs, then the dry ingredients alternating with the molasses and boiling water.
Mix thoroughly and pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: golden flake pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening with pastry cutter to size of peas.
Do not overmix.
Add vinegar, egg and water to flour mixture.
Will make 2 (9-inch) crusts.

title: texas dip
directions: Spread beans on 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Spread on beans.
Mix sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning.
Spread on avocado.
Layer each of remaining ingredients.
Serve with nacho chips.
Chill.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill at least 6 hours.
Mix well before serving.
Garnish each serving with cucumber slices.
Yields about 6 servings.
Store remaining Gazpacho in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: big elsie's methodist punch
directions: Mix juices and water; chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and sherbet.
Serves 40.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt the butter and add to 10x sugar.
Mix very well.
Add peanut butter.
Use your hands to mix well.
Form into small, round balls.
Dip into chocolate coating.
Melt chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
When melted, dip balls with a toothpick.
Fill hole with chocolate using a toothpick.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water according to package directions. In a large buttered casserole dish mix soup, tuna and a little milk.
Add noodles to mixture along with cubed cheese.
Also place chunks of butter throughout.
Add 1 to 2 cups of milk throughout for moisture.
Crush chips over top of casserole. Cover with cheese slices and dot with butter pats.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 - 50 minutes until good and hot and the cheese on top is nicely melted and browned.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown chops and season with salt and pepper; drain off fat. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chops.
Cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in a large skillet and brown meat on all sides.
Transfer meat to a large Dutch oven or roaster.
Add all the remaining ingredients, except the potatoes, to the roaster.
The liquid should cover the vegetables and meat. Add more broth or water if necessary.
Cover and bake for 2 hours. Turn the beef after 1 hour.
Add the potatoes to the pan, increase the oven temperature to 400° and bake uncovered for about 1 hour longer, until meat and potatoes are tender.
Turn meat every 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar until blended. Blend in 9 ounces Cool Whip and pour into pie shell and refrigerate.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Boil spinach in salt-seasoned water in saucepan until completely thawed.	Fry bacon and onions on medium heat in skillet. Crack eggs into large mixing bowl and add 4 slices of cheese, torn into small pieces.	Mix thoroughly.
Add bacon and onions, fried, to mixture.
Drain boiled spinach and add to mixture; mix again. Salt and pepper to taste; mix thoroughly.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish with lid.
Top with remaining cheese torn into pieces to cover top of casserole.
Cover; bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Pour milk over 1 cup bread crumbs; set aside for a few minutes.
Combine cooked squash, onion, 1 tablespoon melted butter or margarine, eggs, garlic salt and pepper; blend well.
Add bread crumbs mixture; stir to blend.
Spoon into a 1-quart casserole that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
This cake can be soaked in brandy, if desired.

title: pork chops with barley
directions: Mix
sauerkraut,
water,
onions,
barley, brown sugar, bouillon, caraway
seed
and
pepper
in a 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Season chops with herbs, lemon juice, salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon
Worcestershire sauce.
Trim chops; brown in skillet. Arrange chops
on
sauerkraut
mixture.
Mix catsup and 2 teaspoons
Worcestershire
sauce
and spread over chops.
Bake in 350°
oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
May be served with baked potatoes.

title: watermelon preserves
directions: Trim off all green rind and any remaining pink meat.
Cut rind into 1/2-inch squares.
Dissolve alum in enough water to cover rind; let stand overnight.
Drain and weigh (6 pounds).
Slice lemon very thin; remove seeds.
Put all ingredients in large pot with 1/2 cup water.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bring to a boil; simmer until melon is clear.
Skim out melon pieces.
Boil syrup until heavy.
Return fruit; bring to boiling point.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend and press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: punch bowl chocolate cake
directions: Bake
chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Pour into 9
x 13-inch
pan.
Cool.
Poke	holes in top and pour Kahlua over cake.
Cut	in
crumble cake and put 1/2 of cake in punch bowl.
Pour
1/2 cooled pudding on cake;
pour 1/2 Cool Whip
over pudding, break 1 Skor bar over Cool Whip and sprinkle on.
Repeat again.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: roast leg of lamb(salt free if desired)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place lamb on a rack in the roaster and insert the garlic slices into the gashes.
Bake for 20 minutes. While lamb is baking, in a bowl combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour over roast.

title: party cookies
directions: Blend shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar-egg mixture, blending well.
Stir in 1/2 cup candies (reserve candies for decorating).

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: While spaghetti is cooking, combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Drain and cool spaghetti.
Once cool, add sauce mixture and serve.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Add sour milk and dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Roll and cut out. Fry in hot fat.

title: sister dot's rhubarb and strawberry jam
directions: Cook the above until clear and then add 1 package of strawberry jello (small box).
Seal in jars.
Red food coloring is optional.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Pat out rolls to solid crust on greased sheet.
Prick thoroughly.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool completely.
Combine other four ingredients and spread on dough.
Top heavily with raw vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Cut to serve cold.
tags: dry Hidden Valley salad dressing mix

title: cheesy corn 'n pasta
directions: In an oiled 3-quart casserole, combine cream-style corn and cheese soup.
Whisk to blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
(If spaghetti is used, break into 1-inch pieces.)
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 minutes or until pasta is cooked.
Casserole will thicken after it is removed from the oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples into a sauce.
Add sugar, vinegar and cinnamon drops.
Boil 20 minutes or so until starting to thicken.
Can while hot.

title: very good noodles
directions: Mix oil, eggs and flour.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll thin, cut in strips.

title: ole suzanne pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and milk.
Toast nuts and add to mixture.
Pour into pie crusts.
Toast coconut and sprinkle over pies.
Add caramel sauce on top of coconut.
Pies are best if frozen 24 hours before serving, then thaw for 1 hour and serve.

title: lima casserole
directions: Place beans in shallow baking dish.
Place small amount of salt on beans, then place soup (no added water) on top.
Bake until boils, then place onions on top and bake until onions are browned (few minutes).

title: fat-free zucchini bread *
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder and set aside.
Beat eggs until frothy; beat in sugar, applesauce and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and flour mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes and invert on racks to continue cooling.
Freezes well.

title: low calorie hot dish
directions: Cut cabbage into medium-size pieces.
Place in greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onion, pour off fat.
Stir rice into meat mixture.
Add salt and pepper, basil and garlic.
Pour meat mixture over cabbage.
Cover with soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer, if necessary.
Serves 6.

title: irish potatoes
directions: In a mixing bowl, put sweetened condensed milk.
Gradually add melted butter, confectioners sugar and coconut.
Roll into small "potato" shapes and roll in cinnamon.

title: banana-sour cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Slice bananas; arrange on bottom of pie shell.
Beat the sour cream, milk and pudding and pie filling (dry) with hand beater until thickened, about 1 minute.
Spread pudding mixture evenly over bananas.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish each serving with whipped cream, if desired.
Top with raspberries.
Tastes best served fresh made.

title: janet's easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk into a saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Mix cake mix with cooked pudding and spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chips over batter and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Cream oil, sugar and egg together.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with milk.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Store in airtight container.
Combine 3 tablespoons of mix with 1 cup boiling water to serve.
Yields 17 cups mix.

title: apple cake
directions: In large bowl, beat together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar immediately after baking and serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: baked alaska
directions: Stir ice cream to soften.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart bowl lined with clear plastic wrap.
Invert ice cream onto cake; remove bowl. Freeze until firm.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: With mixer, mix ingredients.
Add chipped beef and mix well. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix Jell-O according to packages.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemonade concentrate.
Add 1 to 8 cups water.
Add 2 to 4 cups of sugar (6 to 8 cups makes 2 gallons).
Freeze into slush in plastic containers.
Pour ginger ale over fruit juice mixture when ready to serve.

title: apricot-tea delight(ginger ale adds sparkle)
directions: Advance preparation:
Combine hot tea, apricot nectar, orange juice, sugar and lemon juice.
Chill tea-apricot mixture thoroughly.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix and cook at 400° for 8 minutes, then cool.

title: cow pod
directions: Saute pork. Cook rice until tender. Chop tomatoes and cucumber. When done, drain rice. Add eggs and scramble. Add tomatoes, cucumber and pork. Add soy sauce to flavor.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put all ingredients except noodles into a large pot.
Add 2 to 3 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.

title: golden glazed ham
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Score surface of ham.
Heat ham according to instructions on label.
Combine remaining ingredients in small saucepan.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until jelly melts.
Spoon glaze over ham during last 30 minutes of heating time.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and and let dissolve.
Add chocolate chips and let melt.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut to nuts.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven or until top is light brown or cracked.

title: quick bread
directions: Take a half cup of friendship, add one cup of thoughtfulness. Cream together with a pinch of powdered tenderness, very lightly beaten in a bowl of loyalty with one cup of faith, one cup of hope and one cup of charity.
Be sure to add a spoonful of gaiety that sings at little things.
Moisten with tears of heartfelt sympathy. Pound out in a good natural pan.
Must be repeated often in the making of a home.

title: hot spiced cranberry punch
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 10 to 15 minutes. DO NOT BOIL. Makes 50 to 60 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Chill.
Roll in finely chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Take Doritos and place in bottom of a square dish.
Add tomatoes, soup and broth.
Boil on stove until well blended.
Place chicken in mixture and layer with chips in dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes in oven. This can be placed in the microwave.

title: swiss chicken cutlets(put this festive entree together the day before.)
directions: Pound each chicken breast to about 1/4-inch thickness with meat mallet.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Dip in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix bouillon cubes, water, celery, potatoes and onions.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Add carrots and broccoli.
Cook until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup and 1 cup water.
Slowly add Velveeta cheese until melted.
Sprinkle in bacon crumbs.

title: easy extra moist devil's food cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix until blended and beat at medium speed about 2 minutes.
Bake in greased Bundt pan 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute chopped onion in oil in large saute pan.
Add cream of mushroom soup mix, then add chicken broth and splash of white wine. Add shredded chicken pieces, cooked vegetables and frozen peas. Cook until mixture is hot.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine rotini with remaining ingredients except bacon; toss gently.
Cover and chill at least one hour.
Add bacon; toss gently and serve.

title: veggie bites
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Brush bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan with butter or margarine, melted.
Beat egg and water with fork.
Mix flour and salt in another small dish.
Dip 1/4 of veggies into egg mixture.
Remove one piece at a time with slotted spoon, fork or hands.
Roll in flour mixture to coat. Place in pan.

title: poppy seed banana cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cool. Sift powdered sugar over top.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: layered lettuce and vegetable salad
directions: Layer vegetables in 2 or 2 1/2-quart casserole, starting with 1/2 of the lettuce and the other vegetables as they are listed. End with the other 1/2 of the lettuce.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise; spread over salad at least 1/2-inch thick.
Be sure to touch sides of salad.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly and chill overnight.
Delicious! Serves 8.

title: lemon supreme cookies
directions: Melt butter; mix with cake mix and 1 egg.
Mixture will be stiff.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
Beat all remaining ingredients together and pour over crust mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Slice.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain juice off.
Prepare syrup of vinegar, sugar, oil and dill.
Mix well until sugar is dissolved.
Put cucumbers and onion in containers and pour syrup over them.
Put in freezer.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and add sugar gradually. Continue beating until stiff peaks hold their shape.
Fold in cracker crumbs and nuts.
Place mixture in a greased 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator. Next day, fill with whipped cream as pie sinks in the middle as it cools.

title: old-fashioned wilted lettuce
directions: In a small bowl, beat eggs, milk, vinegar, salt and pepper until smooth; set aside.
In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Remove bacon to paper towels to drain, reserving drippings; reduce heat under skillet to medium.
Whisk egg mixture into drippings; cook and stir until thickened, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Place lettuce, onion and bacon in a large salad bowl.
Pour dressing over and toss well.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: green chili cheese hominy
directions: Mix hominy, soups and chili.
Pour into baking dish.
You may add the cheese, layer it, or add to top when baked.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and gradually mix in pineapple.
Add 1/2 cup pecans, onion and salt.
Chill well before forming a ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken legs until done.
Fill a 2-quart saucepan with water.
Add bouillon to taste and thicken with cornstarch, not too thick.

title: campground stew
directions: Cube beef, celery and onions and place in large pot (1 1/2-gallon).
Pour in the pureed tomatoes.
Add water to cover the ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat until celery and onions are done.
Then add cubed potatoes and carrots and peas.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; take out stems.
Mix ingredients.
Add chopped stems to cheese mixture.
Stuff.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes (depending on size of mushrooms) at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put into greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth. Add zucchini and drained pineapple. Fill 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into bowl.
Add the rest; stir with whisk.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in greased casserole dish.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and serve as a dip for fruit.

title: cranberry-jalapeno relish
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the cranberries, orange juice, onion, cilantro, garlic, jalapeno, lime juice, cumin, and salt. Stir together and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except onion rings.
Mix to blend. Chill.
Before serving, fold in onion rings.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Season to taste.
On low heat, add tomatoes, soup and beans.
Stir after each addition. Dice 1/2 the cheese as desired and add to mixture and stir.
Add chips.
Slice remaining cheese and layer on top.
Place in 300° oven until cheese is melted.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on a 12-inch serving platter. Blend avocados, lemon juice and 1/2 cup taco sauce until smooth. Spread on top of bean mixture.
Spread sour cream on top of avocado mixture.
Top with shredded lettuce, cheese, taco sauce and olive slices.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Toss sliced vegetables in large bowl. Mix dressing ingredients. Pour over vegetables. Place in sealed container. Refrigerate. Keeps in the refrigerator 5 to 6 weeks.

title: quick pickled beets
directions: Drain beets well; set aside.
Boil remaining ingredients 2 minutes.
Add beets and boil 1 more minute.
Good served hot or cold.
Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: dirt salad dessert
directions: You will also need a planter, narrow plastic container and flowers.

title: lizzie juday's green tomato mincemeat
directions: Finely chop the suet by hand or in food processor.
Transfer to a large (not aluminum) saucepan.
Put over low heat and cook gently.
Finely chop apples and tomatoes and add to the suet. Stir to mix.
Pour on the cider; add the raisins and bring to a slow bubble.
Thinly slice the orange and remove the seeds.
Chop the slices into tiny pieces and add to the tomato mixture.
Blend in the remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours, or until the mixture has thickened to a juicy relish like consistency.
Cool to room temperature & refrigerate.
May be frozen or canned.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix in a large Tupperware container.
Use generous 1/3 cup per 3/4 cup of boiling water.

title: texas punch bowl cake(yields 22 servings)
directions: Prepare cake mix according to the directions.
Slice strawberries and bananas.
Prepare instant pudding as directed on package.
Layer in punch bowl as follows:
put half of strawberries in bowl and a layer of cake.
Punch holes in layer of cake.
Add half the bananas and half the pudding.
Put layer of cake.
Add all the pineapple and juice, half the strawberries, half the bananas and the balance of pudding.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with whipped topping, coconut and pecans.

title: salami roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put frozen dough in a floured bowl; cover with plastic wrap.
Let dough rise (about 4 hours or refrigerate overnight).
Divide dough into 4 portions.
For each portion of dough, roll out into rectangle.
Lay salami in overlapping rows down center.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Fold in ends and roll from long side.
Lay seal down on cookie sheet; pinch ends as there are no openings.
Brush top with egg white.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Cook pork or beef until tender, then cut up fine and add salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add to meat and tomatoes and cook down low.
Serve hot over hamburger buns.

title: calypso shrimp
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, melt butter.
Saute onion and garlic until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp, rice and chutney; bring to boiling. Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 15 minutes.

title: tomato spinach salad
directions: In a small bowl or jar with tight fitting lid, combine first six ingredients; mix or shake well.
Chill at least 1 hr.
Just before serving, combine spinach and tomatoes in a large salad bowl. Whisk or shake dressing; pour over salad and toss.
(If dressing thickens, thin with additional milk if desired.)

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and biscuit mix in a bowl, adding a small amount of milk, if necessary.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Equal, in saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 10 minutes or until cranberries are soft.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Equal.
You may strain to remove cranberry skins for a smoother sauce.
Cool to room temperature.
Delicious with turkey.
Makes 8 (1/4 cup) servings.

title: caramel (or chocolate) delight
directions: Combine flour, nuts and margarine; bake and cool.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar; spread on crust. Mix pudding; spread over cream mixture and spread Cool Whip on top.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together pudding and pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well and refrigerate.

title: hamburger-noodle soup
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Blend 2 cans of tomato soup and 2 cans of water and heat slowly on low.
In skillet brown ground chuck and onions.
Spoon off excessive fat.
Put in pot with soup. When noodles are done, drain and mix with soup and meat.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season to taste.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt. Add pineapple juice and water. Bring to slow boil, stirring constantly. When thickened and boiling, cook over hot water for 15 minutes. Remove from fire. Add butter, pineapple and beaten eggs. Cool. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put pecans and coconut on bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Prepare cake mix according to package.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix margarine and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar. Drop by spoonful over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Do not frost.

title: noodle dish
directions: Fix the noodles as instructed and drain water.
Add 1 large can of soup to the noodles and cook over low heat until well mixed (no soup lumps).
Open and drain cans of mixin chicken.
Add cans to the noodles and mix well.
Fix about 3 cups of rice.
Heat the other large can of soup in another pan.
When rice and soup are ready, then you can serve.
Put cream of chicken soup on top of rice (on your plate).
Makes about 6 servings.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Make jello as directed.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Save the juice.
Drain mandarin oranges.
Add pineapple and oranges to jello.
Slice
bananas
into thin slices.
Let bananas soak in pineapple juice about 5 minutes.
Take bananas out of juice and add to
jello mixture.
Sprinkle almonds over top.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top of almonds.
Refrigerate until jelled.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar, flour, vanilla and walnuts.
Roll into a ball the size of a walnut.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown in color.
Roll in powdered sugar for covering.

title: cabbage borscht
directions: Combine broth, tomatoes, cabbage, celery, carrots and onions in sauce pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir in sugar and beets.
Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Ladle into bowls.
Top with fresh dill and sour cream, if desired.
Makes 9 cups.

title: something
directions: Saute onion and pepper in skillet.
Add ground beef.
Season with salt and pepper and brown.
Stir in milk and soup.
Layer macaroni, meat and cheese.
End with cheese on top.
Bake at 300° to 350° until bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Note: May add M&M's, pecans, chocolate chips or butterscotch chips, etc.

title: delicious sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add oil and eggs and mix well.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Form balls the size of walnuts.
Press down with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cajun potato salad
directions: Chop potatoes into small pieces.
Combine potatoes, celery, onion and pickle into a bowl.
Add next 5 ingredients, mix gently and chill until serving time.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Put meat, wine, water, bay leaves and spices into a glass bowl and cover.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days.
Baste frequently and turn over once a day.
Then drain meat.
Saving liquid, sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot fat on all sides; add marinade, onions and carrots.
Cover.
Cook slowly for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat in skillet over medium heat.
Drain fat and set aside.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients and meat.
Pour into pastry shell and bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top and knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: sour cream-potato salad
directions: Toss potatoes lightly in butter.
Chop onions and tops; reserve small amount of tops.
Add onions to potatoes.
Chop egg whites; add to potato mixture.
Add celery, salt and pepper; toss lightly.
Mash egg yolks; add to potatoes.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise, mustard and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour over potato mixture; toss.
Garnish with reserved onion tops.

title: baked fish in white sauce
directions: Fold fish in half and place in casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Melt butter; stir in flour and milk in separate pan. Cook until thick and bubbly.
Add mustard; pour over fish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: For Crust:
Mix together flour, brown sugar, margarine and pecan pieces.
Press in a pizza pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Let cool.
Watch crust; don't let burn.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for several hours.

title: beef italiano
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes, beef broth, salt, pepper, oregano and basil.
Cut up tomatoes while stirring.
Heat to boiling.
Add Minute rice.
Reduce heat. Cover for 5 minutes.
(Makes 4 servings.)

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix tomatoes and salt thoroughly; let stand overnight.
Drain. Combine with chopped onions, green and red pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Tie spices in cheesecloth; add to tomato mixture.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.

title: spaghetti squash alfredo
directions: Stab squash several times (to keep it from exploding) and put it in your microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes.
Then slice it open and scoop out and discard the seeds.
Now take a fork and start scraping at the "meat" of the squash.
Simply stir in everything else.
Stir until the butter is melted and serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together hard-cooked eggs, sugar, vinegar, beaten eggs, mustard, mayonnaise, onion and celery.
Mix macaroni and other ingredients together.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 8 to 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in 2-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Coat inside of large Dutch oven with nonstick cooking spray. Saute onion and apple until tender.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until about 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 10 servings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter; add flour, salt and pepper.
Add cheese to mixture.
Place mixture in cookie gun.
Squeeze out mixture in 2-inch straws on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken fettucini
directions: Boil chicken and cut into small chunks; set aside broth.
Saute onion, mushrooms, peas, chicken and milk in butter.
Season to taste.
Boil fettucini noodles in chicken broth.
Mix all together.

title: sausage stuffed mushroom bites
directions: Brown and drain sausage and onions. Wash mushrooms; discard stems.
Place mushroom cups (cavity side up) in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Prepare chicken gravy mix as directed on package. Add all ingredients except cheese and mushrooms to gravy.
Mix well.
Divide mixture evenly in each mushroom cup.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Will also need toothpicks.

title: pepperoni potato bake
directions: Slice potatoes; arrange in bottom of dish. Salt and pepper to taste. Cut butter in small pieces and add with onion slices. Bake in 300° oven until potatoes are tender. Top with cheese, half of tomato sauce, pepperoni and remaining tomato sauce. Bake until cheese melts.

title: bacon and egg salad
directions: Core, rinse and thoroughly drain lettuce.
Refrigerate in disposable plastic bag or lettuce crisper.
Cook bacon crisp; break into medium-large pieces.
Peel eggs; slice 2 of them and coarsely chop remaining 2 eggs.
Combine with salad dressing, sour cream, onion and mustard.
When ready to serve, cut lettuce into bite-sized chunks.
Layer in chilled salad bowl with crisp bacon and sliced eggs.
Toss with dressing and serve at once.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
On a pizza pan, spread crescent rolls out to cover and press edges together well.
Top with sausage. Beat eggs well.
Pour over sausage; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until crescent is brown.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix together the Parmesan cheese, oregano, parsley, paprika, salt and pepper.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks butter and dip the chicken. Roll chicken in the cheese mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour in a foil-lined pan.

title: beef and rice pie for microwave
directions: Combine green pepper and onion.
Cook on High for 1 to 2 minutes; add meat, bread crumbs and 1/2 can of tomato sauce (4 ounce).
Mix together and pat into casserole dish (like a pie crust).
Mix remaining tomato sauce, spices, water, rice and 1/4 of cheese.
Pour over meat crust; cover with plastic wrap.
Cook at 70% power for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover and add remaining cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes in microwave and then serve.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine eggs and milk in mixing bowl; add dry ingredients and beat smooth at low speed.
If too thick to flow through funnel, add a bit of milk.
In electric skillet, heat 1-inch of corn oil to 360°.
Covering funnel opening with finger, fill funnel; release batter into hot oil in spiral shape, do four at a time. When brown, turn with tongs and brown other side.
Drain on paper towels and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 8 to 12.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add salad dressing and Salad Supreme. Stir until well blended.
Cover and let set in fridge for 24 hours.

title: salmon melts
directions: Mash drained canned salmon with mayonnaise.
Add chopped celery.
Spread on English muffins; top with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup and water.
Shape into patties 1-inch thick.
Brown on both sides.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over and around meat.
Cook slowly in covered skillet about 25 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Heat soup; melt cheese in it.
Stir until all cheese is melted.
To hot mixture, add gelatine which has been soaked in 1/2 cup cold water.
Cool.
Fold in Miracle Whip and salt.
When mixture thickens, add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a fish mold, using stuffed olive slices to decorate eyes.
Chill thoroughly before unmolding on platter.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix with the sour cream, soup and diced onion. Add cheese and then potatoes. Cook in 9 x 13 dish at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello as usual.
When setting, add orange, pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Whip with whisk and add walnuts. Put into pan and mold.

title: easy eggplant chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in a strip of bacon; lay in bottom of shallow, ovenproof dish.
Pour soup and sour cream over the chicken.
Sprinkle almonds over soup.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Remove foil and let it brown slightly. Serve over rice.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion in fat.
Add meat and brown, stirring fill broken up.
Add potatoes, carrots, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add tomato soup and water if needed to make right consistency.
If desired, tomatoes that have been put through a sieve may be used. If you use tomatoes, add 1 tablespoon sugar.
Simmer for a half hour or longer.
Stir often.

title: cheesy new potatoes
directions: Slice unpeeled potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Cook in boiling salted water in saucepan until tender; drain.
Layer half the potatoes, cheese and bacon in greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour 1/4 cup butter over top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400°
for 15 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together chicken, green chilies and green chili salsa.
In another fairly large bowl, mix together cream and salt.

Heat about 1-inch of oil in a small frying pan. Dip each tortilla into hot oil for about 3 seconds, just to soften. Drain on paper towels and lay into bowl containing cream. Fill each tortilla with chicken mixture. Roll them up and place into ungreased baking dish.
Pour extra cream over the enchiladas and sprinkle on the cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: carrot juice
directions: Wash and cut carrots in chunks.
Put 2 cups water in blender. Turn blender on blend; while blender is going, drop chunks of carrot in water.
After all carrots have been blended, separate pulp from liquid by straining.

title: heavenly bits
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and salt.
Add vanilla.
Add flour to butter mixture and mix well.
Add nuts and mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.
When slightly cooled, roll in confectioners sugar.
Roll again when cold.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 muffin cups.
Mix shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and egg.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg alternately with milk.
Fill muffin cup 2/3 full.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Sprinkle tops with the mixture.
Bake until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water and let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients into jello and pour into oblong baking dish.
Chill.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with electric mixer until stiff.
May take 10 minutes.

title: streuseled apples(microwave recipe)
directions: In 8-inch square dish place apples and 1/4 cup sugar.
With pastry blender mix flour, 1/3 cup sugar, oats, butter or margarine and cinnamon until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of apples. Microwave on Auto Cook Code 2 or on 20% power for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: flowerpot pudding
directions: Crumble cookies and put in bottom of flowerpot.
Mix pudding mix and milk.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese, cool whip and powdered sugar, and then stir both
together.
Mix well and spread over cookie layer.
Top with remaining crushed cookies. Place gummy worms into mixture, leaving 1/2
to 1 inch sticking out. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cuban roast pork
directions: Make pockets in the pork roast every 2 inches all over.
Smash all garlic clove.
Throw away peel.
Continue smashing garlic until fine.
Combine black pepper, salt and garlic into a paste.
Stuff the pork roast and bake at 375° for 5 to 6 hours.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix together the oatmeal and cocoa.
In pan on stove, add the margarine, milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil; boil for about 3 minutes.
Add the vanilla, then pour over the oatmeal mixture.
Stir well.
Dish out by tablespoons onto wax paper on table.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, crushed potato chips, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy cheese wafers
directions: Mix by hand softened cheese and margarine.
Add other ingredients gradually and alternately pinch off small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in boiling water.
Add frozen orange juice. Add oranges and pineapple and let congeal.
Mix Dream Whip with 1/2 cup of milk.
Blend in pudding mix and rest of milk.
Spread over top of jello.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Sift flour with baking powder. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, extract and coconut. Turn into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven; set temperature at 300°.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Can be iced with any white icing and coconut added.

title: taco casserole
directions: In a large skillet fry ground meat and onion.
Cook until the pink is out of the meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
In a casserole dish, lay bottom of pan with taco shells, then layer of meat; repeat steps and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: fudgesicles
directions: Mix and pour into popsicle molds.
Freeze.

title: penuche
directions: Mix sugar and milk, then add Crisco, vanilla, salt and nuts. Boil to soft ball stage (238°).
Cool without stirring.
When lukewarm, beat until creamy.
Pour into greased pan.
When cold, cut into squares.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form in ball, using extra powdered sugar or flour, if needed.
Roll out in a circle on a floured surface. Spread peanut butter and roll up, using flour with wide spatula. Put on buttered plate in refrigerator until it sets, then slice and serve.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first five ingredients in order listed.
Spread mayonnaise over top to look like a seal.
Sprinkle cheese over mayonnaise.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add bottle of Bac*Os and toss when ready to serve.

title: oven barbecued steaks
directions: Cut steak into about 10 equal portions.
Brown in oil in skillet on both sides.
Place in roasting pan.
Saute onion in oil; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer together for about 5 minutes.
Pour over steaks.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 2 hours or until fork-tender.
Yield:
5 to 6 medium servings.

title: lisa's tortilla soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortilla chips.
Let simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with crumbled tortilla chips in a bowl.
Leftovers can be frozen.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, and salad oil.
Add buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla.
Stir well.
Then add flour, cocoa, baking soda, salt, cloves, baking powder, and zucchini.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes and all other ingredients in a Pyrex dish. Bake in a slow 325° oven for
1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl. Add all remaining ingredients, except walnuts.
Mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread into well-greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool on wire rack and serve when cool.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix
sugar
and
eggs
with margarine. Add flour, mixing well.
Add
nuts.
Make
into balls the size of a walnut and place
on
cookie sheet.
Flatten with palm of hand. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown, in a 375° oven.

title: fresh strawberry sauce
directions: In medium skillet, mix sugar, water and lemon juice. Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes just to boil. Add butter; stir until melted. Mix in strawberries; heat through, but do not cook. Can be used on pancakes, waffles or ice cream.

title: berry mallow yam bake
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, oats and cinnamon.
Cut margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Toss 1 cup crumb mixture with yams (drained) and cranberries.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
With fork, mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening until coarse crumbs.
Add sour cream.
Knead dough 6 to 8 times.
Roll out and cut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 30 minutes (boneless breasts) or 45 minutes (pieces).

title: cunningham charm school punch
directions: Mix Real Lemon and Karo together; add ice.
Pour remaining ingredients.
Drink and be Charming!

title: chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pans.
Measure all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pans.
Bake in an oblong pan for 40 to 45 minutes.
Layer pans for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Ice with Peanut Butter Topping.

title: gay's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add buttermilk and mix well. Add oil and stir well.
May add small amount more of milk, if needed.
Shape into biscuits and place in oiled heavy skillet. Oil tops.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in hot oven (400° to 425°).

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Boil these ingredients for 8 to 10 minutes, until thick.
Line bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan or an 8 x 8-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Pour boiled ingredients over crackers.
Top with more whole crackers.
Frost with Butter Icing.
Refrigerate several hours before cutting.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, soup and peas in dish. Boil noodles until tender. Add noodles to other ingredients. Crumble chips on top of casserole. Bake uncovered at 325° or until bubbling.

title: bar-b-q
directions: Fry hamburger, drain. Add the mushroom soup and chili sauce. Heat through.

title: marinade vegetable salad
directions: Drain these ingredients.
Pour the first mixture over the second mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
The longer it sets the better it is.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat.
Add paste, tomato sauce and remaining ingredients except cooked macaroni. Cook about 20 minutes on low to medium heat.
Stir often.
Stir in macaroni and serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In heavy pot, saute onion until limp.
Add broccoli and parsley and simmer about 3 minutes.
Stirring, sprinkle mixture with flour and stir until absorbed (2 minutes).
Transfer to blender.
Add chicken broth to fill blender to 3/4 capacity. Blend until liquified.
Return to pot and add remaining ingredients and cheese.
Freezes well.

title: x-tra good dumpling soup
directions: Beat butter with eggs until well blended.
Add flour and salt and stir until thoroughly combined.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into just simmering soup.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: breaded veal cutlet
directions: Cut veal into 6 serving pieces, discarding bone and skin. Beat egg slightly; stir in milk and seasonings.
Dip veal pieces in bread crumbs, then into egg mixture and again into crumbs. Heat oil.
Add veal and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until well brown, turning only once.
Serves 6.

title: becky's pasta salad
directions: Boil a full teakettle full of water.
When it is thoroughly hot, begin to make each package of Jell-O separately.
Use clean, square cake pans and empty the red, yellow and green Jell-O packages, each in a separate cake pan.
Pour two cups of hot water into the first pan.
Stir with a spoon until Jell-O is dissolved completely, then place pan in refrigerator.
Repeat with other two pans of Jell-O until all three are refrigerated.
Let chill until firmly set, about 2 hours.

title: liver fritters
directions: Grind altogether; add egg, bread crumbs (may need more if too thin), salt and pepper.
Drop by large spoonful into hot oil.
I chill before using.

title: angel surprise dessert
directions: In small bowl blend milk into cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Add pudding mix and blend.
Pour mixture over angel cake cubes.
Mix well.
Turn into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread pineapple on top.
Prepare topping mix and spread on top.
Chill several hours.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef in pan.
Put it in a deep dish.
Drain Veg-All and white potatoes.
Cut up the potatoes and put on top of meat.
Then add 1 cup water to each package of brown gravy and cook it on stove.
Remove from stove when bubbling.
Pour it on top of meat and vegetables.
Then mix Bisquick with milk or water until soupy.
Pour it on top of pie.
Cook at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bob's beer batter for fish fry
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in beer until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg.
Heat oil (1-inch deep) in skillet or frypan.
Cut fish fillets into small serving pieces.
Dip in batter, fry in oil until brown and crisp, turning once.
Cook only until fish flakes easily, 4 to 6 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add sugar, Butter Buds, salt and 1 cup of flour; beat until smooth.
Add rest of flour a little at a time; continue stirring until smooth. Cover and let rise until double in a warm place (about 40 minutes).
Spoon batter in 24 muffin cups that have been sprayed with cooking spray.
Fill each about 1/2 full.
Again, let rise until dough reaches top of muffin tins (30 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 24 rolls.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into walnut size meatballs.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
No need to brown first.
Make sauce by combining ketchup, brown sugar, garlic powder, chopped onion and liquid smoke.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add carrots.
Add remaining ingredients; beat for 3 minutes. Place in 3 greased layer pans, 8-inch.
Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add peanuts. Cook.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli as directed and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Use large nutty-buddy type cones.
Put in cones 3/4 cup of cut up fruit, such as: strawberries, bananas, apples, blueberries, raspberries, pears or grapes.
Drizzle with 1 teaspoon granola or finely chopped
nuts.
May dip edge of cone into melted chocolate and sprinkle with tiny candies before filling.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Drain fruit; add lemon and orange juice. Add water to make 3 cups. Heat 2 cups juice; add jello and sugar. Stir until dissolved. Dissolve gelatine in 1 cup cold juice. Add to hot juice. Add other ingredients.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix crab meat, butter, seasoning and enough egg to mold into cakes.
Beat 1 tablespoon of water into the remaining egg and dip the cakes in this mixture; roll into bread crumbs.
Saute until rich brown in frying pan or deep fry at 380°.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Cook hamburger with onion.
Mix tomatoes, salt, pepper, rice, chili powder and meat together in a large bowl, then pour ingredients in a baking pan.
Mix up corn bread and bake until corn bread is done, then serve.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook the cornbread following directions on package.
Cook squash according to package.
Mix the soup with the onion and margarine (melted). Add the cooked squash, cornbread (crumbled) and eggs.
Bake in casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter 2 slices of bread and cut in 1/2-inch cubes.
Cut remainder of bread (not buttered) in 1-inch cubes.
Place 1/2 of unbuttered crumbs in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine chicken, mayonnaise, vegetables, pimento, almonds and seasonings.
Spoon over bread cubes.
Sprinkle remainder of unbuttered crumbs over top of this mix.
Combine eggs and milk and pour over this.
Chill several hours (overnight is even better).
Before cooking, spoon soup (undiluted) over the mixture.
Sprinkle with remainder of bread crumbs and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top the last few minutes of baking time.

title: cherry breeze cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine into 9-inch pie pan.
Press and chill.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk and blend.
Stir in lemon, vanilla.

title: mississippi mud cake and icing
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and cocoa.
Beat in oil, flour and vanilla.
Add coconut and pecans.
Bake in large loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and put 1 jar marshmallow cream over the top while hot.
Let cool and ice.

title: billy's fudge
directions: Place marshmallows, sugar, salt and evaporated milk in a large saucepan (4 to 5-quart size) on medium-high heat until the marshmallows melt.
After they have melted, the mixture will start to boil.
Boil the mixture for 5 minutes.
(Note:
You must stir constantly or the sugar will burn.)
After 5 minutes of boiling, take the saucepan off the heat and quickly beat in the butter (or margarine), the chocolate chips and the vanilla.
Once everything is mixed together, pour it into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in the refrigerator to set.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Mix egg white, milk, water, sugar and salt.
Add pecan halves, covering well.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Take out and stir until separated.
Then return to oven to bake 30 minutes longer or until done.
Check often.
Do not overcook.

title: grandma's lime jello salad
directions: Bring water to boiling; turn heat to low and add cottage cheese, marshmallows and Jell-O.
Stir until cottage cheese and marshmallows are dissolved.
Remove from heat; add mayonnaise, pineapple, milk, pecans and lemon juice.
Stir well.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and chill.

title: boeuf bourguignonne
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove and drain. Add beef cubes and brown well.
Remove beef and set aside.
Brown carrot and onion.
Season with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper; stir in flour.
Add broth and mix well.
Add beef, cooked bacon, tomato paste, garlic, thyme and bay leaf. Cover and simmer several hours.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add mushrooms and cooking wine.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over wild rice.
Enjoy!

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and salt.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish. Top with cornbread mixture.

title: blueberry dessert pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 cup oats and 6 tablespoons margarine at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for top.
Blend egg into remaining crumbs.
Press into prepared pan; bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: peach dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour peaches into a greased pan. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top of peaches.
Top with pecans and margarine.
Bake until bubbly.

title: soggy s'mores
directions: Combine chocolate chips, corn syrup and water in a saucepan. Heat and stir until chips are melted and syrup is smooth.
In a bowl, combine and mix well the graham cracker crumbs, marshmallows, sugar, nuts and salt.
Pour syrup over mixture, reserving 1/2 cup. Mix well and press into buttered 9-inch pan.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to reserved syrup.
Stir until butter is melted.
Pour and spread over top of mixture in pan.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares. Makes 81 pieces.

title: lima bean soup
directions: Place the beans in a saucepan and cover with water. Soak overnight with enough water to cover. Add the onion and green pepper and cook until beans are tender. Add sugar, salt and tomatoes. Cook 15 minutes longer. Remove from heat and press through sieve.
Return to saucepan. Mix flour with a small amount of water and stir into the soup. Bring this to a boil and remove from heat. Add butter and serve.
Makes 1 quart.

title: dorito chicken
directions: Crumble Doritos into a casserole dish.
Spread chicken over chips.
Top with Velveeta.
Spread Ro-Tel over cheese.
In a bowl, mix soups and broth; pour over contents in casserole.
Layer remaining chips and Velveeta, ending with chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Add the sugar, butter, nuts and pineapple in bowl.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Alternate layers of wafers and mixture and set in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda in one bowl.
In another bowl, blend butter, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat in eggs and add flour mixture.
Add nuts and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 4 to 5 minutes, until chips are soft.
Remove from oven and run knife through chips and batter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes more, until nicely brown and center is fairly firm.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill until firm.
Shape into crescents or balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Yields 6 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Use two heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup of boiling water.

title: crab dip
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
Add crab meat, mix and add cheese.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add all the other ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Gradually add powdered sugar. Put into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan; chill about 15 to 20 minutes. Cut into squares after chilled.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: minted pineapple
directions: Dissolve Jell-O gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients, saving can to use as mold.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Pour into the can and one individual mold or a serving bowl.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
(To unmold from can, puncture bottom before dipping in warm water.)
Makes 3 1/4 cups, 6 side salads or 10 relish servings.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cook sausage or bacon.
Drain well and crumble.
Mix milk and eggs together.
Lay cubes of bread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle meat over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Pour milk and egg mixture over that.

title: orange julius
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients and blend until all ice cubes are broken.

title: baked cinnamon french toast(main dish for breakfast or brunch)
directions: Line the bottom of a greased 9 x 13 x 2 baking dish with six slices of bread.
Butter remaining bread and place butter-side up over bread already in the dish.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, cream, sugar and vanilla, mix well.
Pour over bread and let stand for 15 minutes.

Place the baking dish inside a larger dish and pour boiling water into the larger pan to a depth of 1 inch. Bake, uncovered, at 375 degrees for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Top with preserves and whipped cream if desired.

title: pumpernickel bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in sugar and water. Pour boiling water over cornmeal, oil, molasses, potatoes, brown sugar, anise and salt. Mix and allow to cool. Combine with yeast mixture, rye, whole-wheat and enough bread flour to form a manageable dough. Mix until smooth after each addition. Knead with seeds and extra bread flour, about 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic. Let rise covered in greased bowl in a warm area, until double in size. Punch down dough; knead dough 2 or 3 turns. Flatten and shape to fit 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans. Let rise until double. Spray tops with water; sprinkle with seeds. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes; spray with water again. Bake 15 to 20 minutes more or until bread sounds hollow when tapped. Cover top with foil if bread becomes too brown. Remove pans; let cool on wire rack.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix butter, eggs, sugar and coffee.
Add dry ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: peach pie
directions: Slice peaches
to
cover
bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle
with
sugar,
cinnamon, nutmeg and almond flavoring. Sprinkle next
with
cake mix.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: In large bowl combine salt, mustard seed, celery seed, onion, sugar, and white vinegar. Put pickles in jars, cover with vinegar mixture. Put in refrigerator. Keeps for 2 weeks.

title: beef log
directions: Mix well by hand.
Refrigerate at least 15 minutes.
Mix at least 3 more times, refrigerating at least 15 minutes between mixings.
Divide into 3 rolls and wrap in foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Unwrap and lay on rack in pan (cookie sheet).
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 300°.
It will be done, but is red looking.

title: strawberry bread(serves 12)
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in a large mixer bowl. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients, beating well. Stir in strawberries. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack before removing from pan.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place peach slices in large bowl.
Mix sugar, whipping cream and flour in separate bowl.
Pour over peaches; toss.
Turn into pastry-lined pie plate.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Brush pastry lightly with milk.
Sprinkle with sugar if desired.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes, until crust begins to brown and juice begins to bubble in center.
Cool slightly.
Serve plain or topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: texas corn salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Blend in the mayonnaise, lemon juice and spices; mix well and chill.
Spoon into bowl lined with salad greens.
Garnish with cooked eggs.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix well drained sausage and cheese together.
Stuff mushrooms. Top with salsa.
Cook in 350° oven until mushrooms are cooked, about 20 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Break up lettuce and mix with onion, celery and water chestnuts.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread on top of lettuce mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bacon bits. This salad is better left set overnight in the refrigerator until the next day.

title: calabacitas(spanish)
directions: Saute squash and onion in oil until just barely tender. Add garlic, chilies, corn and cheese. Mix well. Put in a 1-quart casserole baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into muffin cups for individual desserts and freeze.

title: garden cheese log
directions: Combine cream cheese, Mexican cheese, and bacon pieces.
Beat until well blended.
Shape into a log that is about 6 to 7 inches long.
Roll in pecans.
Refrigerate.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt oleo and mix into cracker crumbs.
Press crumbs into an ungreased 9x13 pan.
Beat sugar, oleo, vanilla, eggs with a mixer for 20 min.
(no less).
Layer mixture over cracker crust.
Layer of pineapple, layer of bananas, layer strawberries.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over strawberries layer cool whip.
Top with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate 2-3 hours.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Brown flour in drippings to make golden roux.
Add onion, celery, pepper and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, water, okra, Tabasco, salt, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, pepper and shrimp.
Simmer about an hour.
Remove a little liquid and stir file into it.
Add to other.
Careful not to boil after adding file as it will become stringy.
Serve over rice.

title: slush
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil. Remove from heat and chill. Add pineapple juice, orange juice, lemonade and bananas. Pour mixture into one or more containers and freeze. To serve, dilute with lemon lime soda.

title: kentucky bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Turn sweet potatoes into large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until heated through.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash sweet potatoes.
Add sugar, bourbon, butter, and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Turn into 2 quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes or until marshmallows are golden.
Serves 9.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cook chicken 15 minutes and drain well.
Dip in buttermilk. Mix flour, parsley flakes, paprika, salt, pepper, thyme and seasoned salt.
Dredge chicken through mixture.
Place in single layer in baking dish with melted margarine.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, turn chicken and bake 45 minutes.

title: zucchini and cheese
directions: Wash and cut off ends of zucchini. Slice in half lengthwise. Parboil in salted water about 7 minutes. Do not overcook.
Scoop out center of zucchini and drain both pulp and shell.
Drain well. Chop pulp and mix with grated cheese.
Use equal amount of pulp and cheese. Season with pepper, garlic salt and m.s.g.
Place cheese mixture in shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked cushaw squash
directions: Slice and peel squash.
Slice into 1/2-inch squares or slice solid part.
Boil in small amount of salted water.
Lift out after 20 minutes.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle bits of butter over squash and cinnamon and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Grease or spray cookie sheets.
Cream margarine and sugar; add vanilla, then flour.
Fold in chips with spoon.
Don't mix too much.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Set oven at 350°. Sprinkle cookies with powdered sugar; let cool.
Enjoy.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine all of the ingredients.
Knead dough. Pat out on waxed paper. Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake for 12 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix well. Stir over medium heat until it boils and thickens really well. Add 1/2 stick butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Serve over hot, buttered biscuits.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch pie tin.
Spread cranberries over the bottom of the pan.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and nuts and sprinkle over cranberries.
Combine flour, margarine and shortening and add to 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Mix.
Pour batter over berries.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream.

title: rice curry
directions: Cook the rice with margarine and salt.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer for 20 minutes (covered).
Saute bacon and onion.
Fry hamburger (drain off fat); add curry powder. Combine meat, bacon, onion, rice and small can of tomato sauce. Mix well in a casserole.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lattice-top chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, seasoned salt, chicken, broccoli, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Open crescent rolls; separate into two rectangles.
Press together perforated cuts; cut each rectangle lengthwise into 3 strips. Place strips on casserole to form lattice top.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.
Top lattice with remaining cheese and onions. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Make pie crust according to directions on box.
Steam broccoli.

title: dilly dip
directions: Fillet fish paper thin; cut into bite size pieces.
Put in deep bowl.
Squeeze lime juice over the fish until well covered. Ice for 1 hour.
Remove fish from juice.
Pour picante sauce over the fish; mix well.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: tabouleh
directions: Pour boiling water over bulgur; zap in microwave for 10 minutes in a ceramic bowl.
If you don't microwave, you can cook it on your stove top, letting it simmer for 20 minutes.
After cooking, let the bulgur cool to room temperature.
Add vinegar and salt to taste.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Boil 3 tablespoons oleo, brown sugar and corn syrup for 1 minute; pour into an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex pan.
Add pecans.
Use your favorite roll dough, about 8 x 8-inch square.
Spread 2 tablespoons oleo, 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and chill for about 30 minutes.
Cut it into 1/2-inch rolls and place on top of syrup mix in pan.
Let rise 30 minutes or until doubled in size.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place slice of cheese on top of each chicken.
Dilute soup with 1/2 can water and pour over chicken.
Combine croutons with butter and sprinkle over dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine melted butter, sugar, eggs, pecans, coconut, raisins, pineapple and vinegar in a mixing bowl; mix well. Spoon fruit mixture into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set. Makes 8 servings.

title: swedish french toast
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat oiled skillet.
Dip bread in batter; fry on each side until brown.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients with 1 cup of sugar.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Batter will be thin.
Grease and flour bread pan and fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: low-fat rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently, until rice is very tender (about 30 to 35 minutes).

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and milk.
Cook on medium-high; must stir constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Then add well beaten egg yolks.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue and bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in top of double boiler. Place over boiling water.
Beat with rotary beater until stiff peak forms.
Scrape bottom and sides of pan occasionally.
Fold in vanilla.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Sift together and stir in last 4.
Chill dough.
Roll balls the size of small onions in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into greased or sprayed loaf pan. Bake at 300° to 325° about 1 hour.
Do not overbake.

title: sugar jumbles
directions: In a mixing bowl mix the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until fluffy and creamy. Sift the flour, baking soda and salt together and add this mixture to the sugar mixture, mixing thoroughly. Place 1 teaspoonful of the mixture on a lightly greased cookie sheet, place drops about 2 inches apart. Bake in 375 degree oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned. Let cool, remove from baking sheet and serve.

title: praline sauce
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.

title: zucchini, eggplant ratatouille
directions: Cut
eggplant, yellow squash, zucchini and peppers into 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat oil in large skillet and saute onion and garlic
until
onion is tender.
Add vegetables and stir for 2 to 3
minutes.
Add
remaining
ingredients.
Heat to boiling point and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until tender, 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: wrapped chicken breasts(with cranberry sauce)
directions: Poach chicken in mixture of chicken broth, white wine and salt until fork-tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Drain and set aside.
Roll out each strip of Puff Pastry until thin.
Brush each ham slice with mustard.
Wrap each half breast with a slice each of cheese and ham.
Wrap Puff Pastry around each breast, sealing edges with water.
Place on a buttered cookie sheet.
Brush each breast with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden.
Serve with cranberry sauce.

title: cheese, pepperoni, veggie casserole
directions: In a large skillet, stir-fry carrots and margarine.
Then add broccoli, stir-fry.
Add squash last and stir-fry.
Cook until crunchy, yet tender (check carrots first).
In saucepan melt Velveeta, half and half and oregano.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Mix everything together by layering along with pepperoni, noodles and Parmesan. Mix lightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato soup to go mix
directions: STEP 1:
Stir together all ingredients, and store them in a mason jar.

title: irish porridge
directions: Combine water, oatmeal and salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve with granulated raw sugar (available in grocery stores) and milk.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until top springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add beef and onion. Cook, stirring with a fork to break up meat, until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Add soup, water, salt, pepper and rice.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer 3 minutes.
In a 3-quart casserole, place cabbage.
Spoon beef mixture over cabbage layer.
Cover and bake for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: chili enchiladas
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Mix 1/2 chili, 2 tablespoons onion and
1 cup of cheese; set aside.
Stir baking mix and water to a
soft dough.
Gently
smooth dough into
a
ball on floured board. Knead
times.
Divide
dough
into
equal parts. Shape
each part
into
a ball.
Roll each ball into a 5 inch circle
and dust with cornmeal.
Bake circle on hot ungreased cookie sheet about 1 minute on each side or until light brown. Spoon
about 1/3 cup of chili on center of each circle.	Roll up,
place
seam side
down	in
ungreased
baking
dish (9 x 13-inch).
Spoon remaining
chili
over
top.
Sprinkle
with remaining
onion
and cheese.
Bake
uncovered
20 minutes or until
cheese is melted. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Great way to use left over chili.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Scoop out potato, leaving peel intact. Mix other ingredients and re-stuff potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: mock caramel apples
directions: Slice apples in serving dish or individual dessert dishes. Combine cream cheese, brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla.
Beat well over low heat until all is smooth.
Serve in small dishes. This tastes just like the caramel apples on a stick!

title: spanish omelette(tortilla espanola)
directions: Warm olive oil in a large nonstick frying pan.
Add the onion and garlic and fry until done.
Add the potatoes and salt and pepper.
Fry potatoes until done (not too brown).
Remove from heat and drain off the excess oil.
In a large bowl, beat the egg whites with a little water.
Add egg yolks and beat again.
Then add potatoes and onions to mixture and blend thoroughly.
Pour into hot pan.
Do not fold over the omelette but allow the underside to cook.
Keep a spatula moving around the edges to make sure it doesn't stick.
When underside is golden brown, place a plate or pan lid over the pan and slowly up the tortilla onto the plate.
Then replace in pan with the uncooked side down.
Cook until brown.

title: crockpot perfect meatloaf
directions: Using a fork, mix all ingredients, except for catsup.
Shape into a loaf and put into greased crockpot.
Top with
catsup and pepper rings, if desired.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, then on low for 6-8 hours.
Quartered potatoes coated with butter may also be cooked with this recipe.
A dash of paprika will give the potatoes a nice browned look.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour.
Brown meat in frying pan.
Add tomato sauce, onions, mushrooms and red wine.
Let simmer until meat is tender.
Add sour cream 5 minutes before serving.
Serve over noodles (makes 4 to 5 servings).

title: applesauce cinnamon pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
In smaller bowl, mix egg, milk and oil together, then add to flour mixture.
Add applesauce and stir until moistened.
Cook on heated griddle over medium-high heat, slightly oiled, until bubbly and bubbles are bursting.
Turn and cook until underside is golden.
Serve with hot syrup.
Makes 12 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Put milk in a bowl or ice tray and let stay in refrigerator until crystals form. Remove and beat with mixer until whip cream consistency.
Dissolve jello in water. Add sugar, salt and 3 tablespoons lemon juice. Add some grated lemon rind, if desired. Chill until slightly thick. Add jello mixture and whipped milk together.
Line bottom of dish with 1 1/2 cups vanilla wafer crumbs.
Pour mixture on top of crumbs and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top of jello mixture. Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: broiled rock shrimp("danish lobster tails")
directions: Wash and fan or split shrimp (butterfly).
Lay out on cookie sheet.
Melt butter.
Add lemon juice and garlic salt.
Preheat oven on broil.
Pour melted butter sauce over shrimp.
Broil about 15 minutes.
Save some sauce for dipping.

title: bessie's rice
directions: Place in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.
Good with chicken or pork chops.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook onion and bacon together.
Mix with rice, beef and egg; season with salt and pepper.
Wrap in cabbage leaves.
Pour tomato puree over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare devil's food cake according to package directions in jelly roll pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next day cut into 1-inch cubes. Use meat tenderizing mallet to smash candy bars (not down to powder).
Prepare chocolate mousse according to package directions. Layer in transparent large glass bowl or trifle dish:
cake cubes, mousse, toffee pieces, Cool Whip.
Continue layering 2 to 3 layers. Sprinkle top layer of Cool Whip with toffee pieces.
Serves a crowd.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add salt, pepper, sour cream and butter.
Beat until fluffy.
Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This can be made a day ahead, kept in the refrigerator and then baked just before serving.

title: italian chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Season chicken with Lawry's seasoning salt, oregano and pepper to taste.
Place chicken in large bowl; add Italian dressing, vinegar and garlic.
Allow chicken to marinate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Lay chicken flat out in a casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 350° to 400°.
Let chicken bake for 45 minutes to an hour or until golden brown. Serve hot.

title: watergate salad
directions: Refrigerate Cool Whip overnight.
Fold all ingredients together and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
