Grease an 8-inch round cast-iron skillet or a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sift together first 4 dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat together eggs, sugar, buttermilk, melted butter and cornmeal in large bowl (in order).
Stir dry ingredients into buttermilk mixture.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serve warm with chile or beans!
Makes 12 servings.

title: baked rice with sausage
directions: In a large skillet, cook sausage, onion and green pepper over medium heat until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender; drain.
In a large saucepan, bring water to a boil; add dry soup mix.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 5 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in canned soup, rice, sausage mixture and mix well.
Transfer to a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Toss bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over rice mixture.
Bake uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and add to noodles.
Mix well.
Put into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients, add the next 6 ingredients.
Fold in stiff beaten egg whites.
Pour in three 9-inch cake pans, greased and floured.
Preheat oven and bake at 350° for 30 minutes (golden brown).
Cool for 10 minutes, then on rack.

title: honey butter
directions: Whip margarine with electric mixer; blend in honey and cinnamon.

title: barbecued ribs for grill
directions: Salt and pepper ribs.
Sprinkle with dried mint.
Start fire in smoker.
When flame has died, place small chunks of presoaked hickory wood in water; put on coals.
Place ribs on grill.
Do not let fire get too hot.
If you don't have a smoker, use regular grill with lid.
Put coals to one side, ribs on the other side. Cook until tender.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Beat mixture until creamy.
Add milk slowly. Add salt.
Put in double boiler.
Add rice.
When mixture is hot, add the cornstarch which has been dissolved in a little water. Stir until thick.
Take off fire. Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Put in pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar (1/2 cup).
Spread over pudding. Bake in a 425° oven until brown.

title: egg rice salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator to chill. Mold.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaf.
May garnish with tomato wedges.
Serves 6.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Layer onions, potatoes, hamburger, rice and celery in greased 2-quart casserole, seasoning each layer with salt, pepper and paprika.
Mix soup and water; pour over celery.
Bake covered for 2 hours at 375°.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Place egg yolk in bowl; beat well, then add shortening and buttermilk. Add all other ingredients except egg whites. Mix well. Beat egg whites stiff, then fold in. Cook in waffle iron.

title: potato broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Add flour and seasonings.
Add milk; cook slowly until bubbly.
Add cheese and potatoes; put half of mixture into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with broccoli.
Top with remaining mixture.
Cover; bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in melted fat.
Add tomato juice, mushrooms and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for one hour.
Add shrimp and cook for 30 minutes longer.
Thicken with paste made from flour and 1/2 cup water.
Serve over rice.

title: clam stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix cream cheese with onion and soup.
Add the can of minced clams and some juice if necessary.
Stuff in mushroom caps.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
If desired, freeze in pie pans.
To serve, defrost and reheat at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into ice cream freezer; freeze.

title: never fail oil crust
directions: Stir together with fork the flour, wheat germ and salt. Combine oil and water in separate container.
Stir oil and water mixture all at once into flour.
Stir until flour is all dampened. Divide into 2 balls.
Roll out each ball between 2 sheets of waxed paper until size for crust.
(To keep paper from shifting, dampen area where paper is placed.)
Bake shells in a 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Yields 2 large crusts.

title: chicken a'la orange
directions: Fry chicken 1/2 done (coat it with flour).
After 1/2 done, place chicken in sauce and bake 1 hour or less at 350°.
Garnish with sliced oranges.

title: cran-apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
This will be very thick.
Fold in chopped pecans, cranberries and peeled apples.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in tube pan.
Great with coffee.

title: chicken in mushroom gravy(crock-pot)
directions: Place chicken pieces in Crock-Pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix liquid and soup; pour over chicken.
Add mushrooms. Cover and cook on Low 7-9 hours (High:
3-4 hours).
Recipe may be doubled for a larger Crock-Pot.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix sugar into softened cream cheese.
Add vanilla.
Prepare Lucky Whip in a cold bowl.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Put into crust and top with pie filling.
Chill.

title: father's fish house punch
directions: Three days prior to serving, heat water and sugar to boiling; stir to form syrup.
Cool.

title: corn cakes
directions: Put the corn meal, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl.
Pour the boiling water over them.
Let this stand until the corn meal swells, then add the cold sweet milk.
When cool, stir in the flour and baking powder; mix well.
Add well beaten egg.
Bake on hot griddle until cooked through and well browned.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Stir in sauce, paste, sugar, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook and drain noodles.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, peppers and green onions. Spread noodles in baking dish; top with 1/2 of meat mixture. Cover with cheese.
Add more noodles and more meat to layer. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook Italian sausage, onion and green pepper.
Drain; cook noodles and drain.

Mix Italian sausage, noodles, sauce, pepperoni, mushrooms, salt, pepper and garlic salt in baking dish. Cook at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, then top with Mozzarella cheese and cook another 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach calzone
directions: Squeeze water out of spinach and put in bowl.
Add olive oil and garlic powder.
Mix with a fork.

title: kugelis-lithuanian potato pudding
directions: Grate potatoes to coarse (food processor can be used).
Cut bacon into one-inch lengths and fry to crisp.
Add chopped onions to bacon and saute to clear.
Add butter or oleo to mixture until melted.
While cooling, mix potatoes, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add bacon mixture and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares and serve hot with sour cream.

title: cracker pie(mock apple pie)
directions: Combine water, sugar and spices, bring to a boil.
Pour into unbaked pie shell, in which the 12 saltine crackers have been broken up, then dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: carrots with basil
directions: Slice carrots diagonally.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add carrots and a pinch of sugar.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 2 teaspoons of basil.
Cover and steam about 20 minutes.

title: communion bread
directions: Mix well with a fork 1 cup flour, Crisco and salt.
Add honey and milk to mix with consistency to roll out flat.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: chicken and potato salad
directions: Remove skin and pull chicken or turkey from the bones.
Pull the meat into shreds.
Set chicken aside.
Boil unpeeled potatoes for about 20 minutes, until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: cheesy mexican chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size and cook in Microsteamer (6 to 8 minutes). Mix soup, milk, seasoning mix and 1 1/2 cups of cheese. Place 1/3 bag of corn chips in the bottom of the large deep microwave-safe dish. Place chicken on top of chips. Spoon soup mixture over the chicken. Top with corn chips and remainder of cheese. Microwave on High 5 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Core peppers and keep tops.
Salt and parboil peppers and tops in salted boiling water 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from hot water.
Fry onion, hamburger and bread until brown.
Mash up can of tomatoes.
Pour off juice.
Mix tomatoes and hamburger (off fire when done, not when cooking).
Stuff peppers.
Put in deep casserole.
Pour tomato juice over stuffed peppers.
Add water, if necessary.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain and add cream soup, cheese and 1/4 stick oleo; set aside.
Saute onions in 3/4 stick oleo until tender.
Remove onion from oleo; add to broccoli mixture.
Pour entire mixture into a casserole dish.
Mix together remaining oleo and crackers.
Press on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: ham and peaches
directions: Preheat broiler.
Sprinkle peaches with 1 tablespoon rum.
Let stand.
Slash fat around ham.
Stud with cloves.
Broil 5 minutes on one side.
Meanwhile, combine remaining rum with sugar and mustard.
Turn ham.
Broil 3 minutes.
Arrange peaches around ham. Spread mixture over steak and peaches.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes more or until just glazed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients. Form into small balls. Fry in deep fat until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine chili sauce and grape jelly.
Dump bag of meatballs in crockpot.
Pour mixture over meatballs.
Let simmer. Serve.

title: any fruit coffee cake
directions: In medium saucepan, combine fruit and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes or until fruit is tender.
Stir in lemon juice.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cornstarch; stir into fruit mixture and cook and stir until thickened.
Cool.

title: good corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Mix with corn and soup.
Add cheese.
Bake until hot.
That's all.
Really good with a lot of Velveeta.

title: carolyn gough's ooey gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, 1 egg and pecans.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Will be crumbly.
Then mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Spread on top of cake mix.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not cut until cooled.

title: red-hot chicken wings
directions: Cut each wing into thirds, discarding tips.
Broil wings for 5 minutes; turn over and broil 5 minutes longer.
Watch carefully to prevent burning.
In a saucepan, combine hot sauce and butter; heat until butter melts.
Place chicken wings in a large pan with some of the sauce; shake to coat well.
Serve with a sauce dish of Blue cheese dressing as a dip.
(After coating, chicken wings may be refrigerated and then reheated at 350° for 10 minutes.)
Yields 30 pieces.

title: zesty crabmeat spread
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except paprika; mix well.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Before serving, sprinkle with paprika and garnish as desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients very thoroughly. Press out in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake until light brown (15 to 20 minutes) at 325°. Let cool.

title: bear track cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Blend in chocolate, vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Insert about halfway into fattest side of each, 4 peanut halves to resemble claws.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, mix butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
After smoothly mixed, add dry ingredients, then add chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet (may spray with Pam, if desired) in preheated oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add other ingredients (potato chips last) until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon on a lightly greased and floured cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not bake too dark.
While warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: american flag cake
directions: Slice 1 cup strawberries and set aside. Cut cake into 10 slices. Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish with cake slices. Top with 1 cup sliced strawberries, 1 cup of the blueberries and all the whipped cream. Place strawberry halves and remaining 1/3 cup blueberries on the whipped topping to create a flag design. Refrigerate until ready
to serve.

title: broccoli and macaroni hollandaise
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Fold in mayonnaise.

title: oven stew
directions: Sprinkle beef with flour mixed with seasonings.
Toss with oil in a 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes. Stir once.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce and water over all.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add juice of lemons. Beat egg yolks and add to mixture.
Slowly add boiling water.
Cook until thick.
Add salt.
Pour in baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks.
Add 3 tablespoons of sugar and a sprinkle of salt.
I also add a few drops of vanilla or lemon juice to the meringue.
Pile on lemon filling in crust.
Brown in oven. This recipe takes either 1 1/2 or 3 of each ingredient.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.
Brown and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and next 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook, then dice the potatoes. Cook macaroni.
Add potatoes and macaroni to pot.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in frozen veggies.
Return to a boil.
Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Yield:
12 cups.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add the tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes, covered.
Stir several times. Cook egg noodles 8 minutes. Alternate layers, beginning with noodles, sauce, sour cream, cheese, etc.
End with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, and drain. Tear crab into pieces, slice celery and green onions. Add these and black olives together.
Squeeze lemon over mixture.
Add just enough mayo to moisten.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Can also put these in muffin tins for a decorative touch.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into baked and cooled 8 inch graham cracker crust.
Top with pie filling.
Chill or freeze.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Mix in milk and vanilla. Separate eggs.
Keep the whites for meringue.
Bake 9-inch pie shell.

title: salsa
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and simmer 2 hours.
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: rhineland potato salad
directions: Cook bacon, onions and pepper until bacon is crisp.
Drain and add to remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Bake in an oblong pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: praline cookies
directions: Combine milk and sugar in top of double boiler; cook until well blended, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter. Cool slightly.
Add gradually to beaten egg.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop from tablespoon, about 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour over chicken wings in baking dish.
Cook 2 hours at 250°.
Keep turning.

title: czech ham cabbage and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package until just barely tender.
Drain.
In a skillet melt butter and saute cabbage until tender.
In 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole place a layer of half the noodles, then half the cabbage and all the ham.
Then layer the rest of the cabbage and noodles on top.
Scald the milk and slowly add to the beaten eggs, beating constantly.
Add salt and pepper and beat well.
Pour over casserole layers and bake at 350° about 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: like 409 cleaner
directions: Mix together and use.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and oleo and mix well. Add eggs, milk and vanilla to this mixture.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Place broccoli spears on bottom of baking dish.
Break up chicken over top.
Mix soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Pour on top. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter. Sprinkle on top.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp and crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers in butter. Add cream of mushroom soup. Cook about 15 minutes. Add peeled shrimp and crab meat. Cook on medium to low heat for 10 to 15 minutes. Mix together with 1 1/2 to 2 cups cooked rice. Season well and pour into buttered casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 325 for 30 minutes. Last 5 minutes; top with cheese.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place a thick layer of raw potatoes in a casserole dish which has been buttered.
Sprinkle rice over potatoes.
Cover rice with ground beef.
Add layer of chopped carrots, then green peppers, onions, salt and sugar.
Add tomatoes which you have chopped up with the juice.
Cover tightly and cook at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage, parboil rice and saute onions in oleo or oil.

title: rolled parmesan chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine Parmesan and bread crumbs.
Dip each chicken breast into margarine then roll in cheese mixture.
Roll chicken and place in baking dish seam side down.
Sprinkle top of chicken rolls with additional Parmesan. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add mushroom soup, water and milk. Stir well and bring to a boil.
Pour in 4 cups egg noodles and stir well.
Boil for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour in cheese cubes and stir until cheese melts.
Lower heat and add tuna.
Simmer until hot.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir and serve immediately.

title: aunt betty's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, beaten egg, horseradish, salt, ketchup, milk and Lawry's seasoning salt.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cut apples in quarters. Roll each biscuit out thin and cut in half. Roll 1 piece of apple in dough (20 pieces of apples and 20 pieces of dough). Place in baking dish. Heat sugar, water, margarine, vanilla and cinnamon. Pour over apples. Sprinkle a little cinnamon on top. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine butter, flour, salt and pecans.
Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 15 minutes or until light brown at 350°.
Cool.

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs; add salt.
Beat well until foamy.
Add flour, enough to handle dough.
Roll thin; let dry and cut and set awhile.
Add to boiling broth.
Cook until tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook broccoli for 5 minutes, drain well. Combine soup, mayonnaise, egg, cheese, onion and pepper to taste. Add broccoli and mix together well. Spoon into greased baking dish, dot with butter and sprinkle with crushed crackers. Bake uncovered for 1 hour.

title: black-pepper dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small bowl until thoroughly blended. Spoon into small, covered container and refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Good on hot or cold meat or chicken or instead of sour cream on baked potatoes.
Keeps up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: mother's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and shape into balls.
Cook in spaghetti sauce for 1 1/2 hours on a low flame.

title: applesauce wheat bread(bread maker recipe)
directions: Ingredients should be at room temperature.
Melt butter.
Add to applesauce and water.
Place these in bread pan.
Add all dry ingredients except yeast.
Sprinkle in yeast so it is away from liquid.
Add raisins halfway through kneading cycle.

title: simple brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil until it cleans the sides of bowl. Press in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with chocolate chips and nuts.
Press in.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Test with toothpick.
Cut when cool.

title: pineapple cherry cake
directions: Evenly spread pineapple in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Carefully spread pie filling on top.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until the top is browned.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: a-meal-in-one
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain off fat.
Add 57 sauce, ketchup and seasoning, then add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes with lid on.
Serve over rice.
Freezes well.

title: mrs. j's baked beans
directions: Pick over and wash beans.
Simmer first three ingredients 1 1/2 to 2 hours until just tender, not mushy!
Add water if necessary.
Turn into 2-quart baking pan.
Add next four ingredients.
Bake in slow 300° oven for 2 to 3 hours.
Add water if necessary to keep beans moist while baking.

title: party potatoes
directions: Stir 1/4 cup of the butter into the hot mashed potatoes.
Whip cream cheese with sour cream until smooth and fluffy in the blender.
Add cream cheese-sour cream mixture, salt and pepper to hot potatoes and mix well.
Spoon into buttered casserole.
Melt remaining butter and spread on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie without crust
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth for 2 minutes by hand or 1 minute by blender.
Pour into plate.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut up chicken in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour stock over chicken.
Add soup, salt and pepper to taste.

title: gram's swedish potato dumplings
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until done.
Mash; add sugar and set aside.
Chill.
Fry meat gently; add chopped onion.
Have 1 or 2 pans boiling water to which 1 tablespoon of salt has been added. When potatoes are cold, add eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Flour hands and spread dough over palm.
Fill center with meat mixture. Drop in boiling water and cook 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Place in a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: garden vegetable pasta sauce
directions: In 2 to 3-quart casserole, place oil, celery, carrots and onion.
Cover and microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes until softened. Stir in remaining ingredients and continue microwaving 2 to 3 minutes until hot.
Stir and let stand a few minutes to blend flavors.

title: this-can't-be-tuna dip
directions: In a small bowl, break tuna into small pieces.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with corn chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
Chop onion into fine pieces. Combine onion, broccoli, chicken soup, cooked rice and 1 pack of cheese.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Take the other pack of cheese and sprinkle on top.
Place in 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in potato chips and flour.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Makes about 8 1/2 dozen.

title: bubble bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in lukewarm water and let rise.
Pour in one beaten egg and oil.
Add liquid to flour and salt.
Mix and knead for 5 to 10 minutes, until dough is smooth.
Let rise; punch down and let rise again.
Form dough into little balls and dip in mixture of melted oleo, egg, garlic powder and oregano.
Take balls out with slotted spoon and shake off excess liquid.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, close together, until pan is filled.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until browned.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add soda, cream of tartar and salt and stir.
Immediately pour over popped corn and mix thoroughly.
Place in large pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.

title: thanksgiving day salad(make the day before)
directions: Bring water to a boil in a saucepan over
high heat.
Pour over the gelatin in a mixing bowl.
Stir to dissolve the gelatin. Add the strawberries and cranberry sauce, stirring to break up the sauce.
Stir in the nuts.
Pour into a pretty 2-quart ring mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: blade jewel poppy loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into two lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Add cranberries.
Boil until cranberries pop.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and marshmallows. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into Jell-O mold and chill.

title: pickled aigs
directions: In a saucepan, put all 'cept aigs...bring to a boil 'n simmer fur a few minutes...cool.

title: tim's salad
directions: Combine avocado, tomatoes and dressing; toss lightly.
Chop lettuce finely; place on large platter in single thick layer. Place tomato and avocado mixture on top and garnish with apple slices around edges.

title: rosemary's microwave fudge
directions: Sift sugar, salt and cocoa together into large microwave-proof bowl.
In center of sugar mixture, place butter and milk. Microwave 30 seconds or until butter is melted.
Beat until shiny. Add vanilla.
Beat.
Add nuts, if desired.
Spread in greased 9 x 9-inch dish.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: potato stuffing (side dish)(pennsylvania dutch recipe)
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the onion and celery in butter until tender.
Remove from the heat.
Add bread, potatoes and parsley; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is lightly browned. Yields 6 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat.
Add pepper, catsup, mustard, sugar, salt and vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or less.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for ten minutes or until golden brown. Mix margarine and garlic powder. Brush this over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.

title: dirt cake
directions: Place half of crushed cookies in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Blend the cream cheese and oleo until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and powdered sugar.
In separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla flavoring according to box instructions.
Fold pudding mixture into cream cheese mixture.
Pour filling over cookie crust, then cover with remaining cookies.
Chill before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in graham cracker crusts.
Let set overnight.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook
chopped
frozen
broccoli following directions on package.
Cook rice;
combine these two with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: "one knuckle" rice or perfect rice every time
directions: Put rice in pan; add water to level previously mentioned.
Add salt and butter.
Bring to boil.
Cover and turn to low.
Leave covered for 20 minutes.
Perfect rice every time.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, beating after each addition.
When mixture becomes stiff and hard to beat, add milk, cream, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly before pouring into freezer.

title: jingle bell punch
directions: Can add some vodka to it, also.
Makes 40 (4-ounce) servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Sometimes I shorten this and use like 2 tablespoons water.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil margarine, cocoa, cream and sugar for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and peanut butter.
Stir all together and spoon out onto wax paper.

title: cream cheese chicken
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream powdered sugar, Crisco, vanilla, almond extract and egg. Stir in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Refrigerate mixture 3 hours.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Chill for 1 hour.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise and add marshmallows; add to Jell-O and stir.
Add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip (may not need all of Cool Whip). Let set until jelled, preferably overnight.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cream again.
Add eggs, beating well.
Mix cocoa and coffee; add to creamed ingredients. Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to creamed ingredients, in thirds, with buttermilk.
Beat for three minutes.
Add vanilla and beat about 30 seconds.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Mix boiling water and cocoa and cool.
Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt, vegetable oil and unbeaten egg yolks.
Beat until fluffy and add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Beat 7 egg whites and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Fold into mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 320° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix everything, but hash browns, in large mixing bowl.
Add potatoes and toss.
Put in well-greased, 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 2 cups crushed potato chips or corn flakes.
Drizzle with 1/2 cup melted oleo.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Combine cooked rice, celery, onions, margarine, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with chicken breasts.
Combine soup and yogurt.
Spoon over chicken breasts. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven. Add carrots and top with paprika. Bake 15 minutes more.

title: boston brown bread(no fat, no eggs)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Spoon into well-greased and floured coffee cans (13 oz. size). Fill about half full. Let stand 1/2 hour, then bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: mansion hill salad
directions: In a salad bowl, toss the leaf lettuce, romaine lettuce and red onion with the	olive
oil.
Cut
any
large artichoke hearts into halves or
quarters.
Add
to the lettuce mixture. Season with salt and pepper.

title: egg salad sandwich
directions: Flaked tuna or salmon, sweet pickle, chopped celery and mayonnaise.

title: pudding or oil cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together; beat 5 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in angel food or Bundt pan. Slice and serve with fruit, ice cream or sherbet.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack into an oiled 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch or larger casserole dish or two (8-inch) square dishes.
Make one, freeze one.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: molded pear salad
directions: Drain pears; reserve 1 cup juice and bring to boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in juice.
Mix in cream cheese which has been softened with milk.
When cool, add pears, mashed.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into mold; chill.

title: cranberry pie(serves 6)
directions: Add to cranberry mixture.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling into dish.
Add pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Pour melted butter next.
Put pecans on last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir the first 4 ingredients together.
Cook for 4 minutes on High.
Take out and stir.
Cook 4 more minutes.
Take out.
Add oleo and vanilla; cook 1 more minute.
Take out.
Add the soda; stir gently.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute chopped onion in cube of butter.
Combine all ingredients in roasting pan.
Cook in 200° oven for 4 hours.
Stir often.
Makes 5 quarts.
Good to freeze.

title: chicken rice and cheese
directions: Chop onion and cook in oil until tender.
Add broth; heat until boiling.
Add rice.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add chicken, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat until cheese melts. Serves 6.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix margarine, flour and sugar together.
Pat into a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Let cool.

title: beef salad vinaigrette
directions: Trim roast of all fat and gristle.
Cut into julienne pieces 1/4 inch by 1 1/2 inches.
In small bowl combine vinegar, salt, pepper and mustard.
Whisk in oil until mixture is well blended. Add garlic powder.
Pour mixture over meat and mix well.
Cover and marinate 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish with onion, hard-boiled eggs, pickles and tomatoes.
Serve with hot French bread, if desired.

title: london chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Then brown mushrooms.
Place chicken in casserole.
Mix soups (undiluted) and pour over chicken.
Put mushrooms on top.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
When ready to bake, add wine.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Good with rice.

title: honey bear's hot chocolate
directions: Combine chocolate and water in a large saucepan.
Stir over low heat until chocolate melts.
Add sugar and salt.
Simmer 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add milk; stir and heat; do not boil.
Pour into mugs.
Top with whipped cream and dash of nutmeg. Serves 4.

title: sweet dough
directions: In a large bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Combine milk, water and margarine in saucepan; heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Margarine does not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap, then a towel. Set aside 20 minutes.
Turn dough out onto heavily floured board. Divide dough in half.
Roll each half into a 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Fill with choice of fillings.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch square baking pan; set aside.
In bowl cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour and blend well.
With hands, gather up dough and press evenly over bottom of pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until pale golden brown.
Transfer pan to wire rack and cut into small squares.
Let cool in pan.
Makes 25 squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup stuffing.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup herb stuffing. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in dry place.
Use either hot or cold, 1 rounded teaspoon per cup or glass.

title: sauteed zucchini with raisins*
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise and cut into slices 1/2-inch thick.
In large frying pan, heat 1 tablespoon of the oil and 1 tablespoon of the butter over medium-high heat.
Add half the zucchini and brown on both sides.
Add remaining oil and butter and saute rest of zucchini.
Remove with a slotted spoon. Dissolve 2 teaspoons salt in the vinegar.
Remove hot pan from heat and add vinegar, stirring up any browned bits.
Return zucchini to pan with raisins and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Cook over medium-high heat until zucchini is tender, 10 to 20 minutes. Taste for seasoning and add salt and pepper if needed.
Serve immediately or reheat when needed.

title: cherries jubilee fruit salad
directions: Drain cherries, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
In medium saucepan, combine gelatin and syrup mixture.
Heat and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat; stir in sherry.
Chill until partially set.
Reserve 2 pear halves; slice and set aside for garnish.
Chop remaining pears; fold into gelatin along with cherries.
Chill until firm.
Unmold; garnish with lettuce leaves and pear slices.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 8.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and Cool Whip until smooth.
Spoon into crust and smooth.
Pour on pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: orange tropical salad
directions: Boil Jell-O, tapioca and water 4 minutes.
Add Mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.
Mix and refrigerate 4 or 5 hours.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well and form long rolls with dough.
Chill through.
Cut into thin slices.
May decorate with pecan halves. Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: bite-size cheese cakes
directions: Mix cheese and egg yolks until fluffy.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Use mini-muffin tins.
Butter generously.
Pat approximately 1/2 teaspoon graham cracker crumbs in each cup. Shake to lightly cover bottom and sides.
Fill tins with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Top with blueberry or cherry pie filling.
Remove carefully to a pretty glass serving piece.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Put chicken broth, water and bouillon cubes in a large pot. Add potatoes and onions. Boil until potatoes are tender. Reduce heat and add cream of celery and cream of mushroom soups. Add Cheez Whiz. Stir until melted. Top with bacon bits, if desired.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fry in shortening to cover until golden brown.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in quarters (wedges).
Place in strainer; rinse. Place in Dutch oven.
Sprinkle cabbage with salt and pepper.
Slice corned beef.
Place two slices on top of each wedge (quarter) of cabbage.
Steam on medium heat about 20 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup water if needed; test for doneness.
Do not overcook cabbage.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt
butter
in single layer cake pan or iron skillet. Add brown
sugar
and
dissolve, then add pineapple.
Combine flour, sugar,
egg and milk and pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt to a hard boil stage, 250°.
Put Creme in a mixing bowl and stir in hot syrup.
Beat until stiff and stands in peaks.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto a waxed paper.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Add buttermilk.
Add melted margarine. Pour in crusts.
Makes one 9-inch deep dish pie or 2 regular pies.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken squares
directions: Mix
chicken,
celery,
mayonnaise,
soup,
rice, lemon juice, onion
and salt and pepper.
Mix well and spread into a 12 x 8-inch
greased baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can substitute chow mein noodles for crumbs.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add milk and molasses, beating well.
Add sugar, flour, salt, nutmeg, allspice and melted butter.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until set.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 9 inch pie shell and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, confectioners sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter until it resembles coarse meal.
Beat egg until light.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons beaten egg and vanilla extract over mixture.
Blend well.
Form into a ball.
Dough may be chilled, if desired.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Place the broccoli in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, put the chicken on top. Combine the soup, milk, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry.
Pour over the top of the chicken.
Sprinkle the top with cheese and croutons.
(Optional:
Drizzle melted butter on top.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over or with rice or noodles.

title: potato omelet
directions: Cook chopped onion in hot cooking oil or shortening in a 10-inch skillet until tender, but not brown.
Add sliced potatoes. Cover and cook about 18 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring gently occasionally.
Drain.
Add beaten eggs to the skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook without stirring until egg mixture begins to set on bottom and edges of the skillet.
Using a spatula, lift egg mixture so uncooked portion flows underneath.
Cook about 3 minutes more or until eggs are cooked throughout but still glossy and moist.
Slice omelet onto a serving plate and cut into wedges.
Sprinkle hot omelet with shredded Cheddar, if desired.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in mixer; add eggs and add sugar, mixing well. Add ingredients in a floured and greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix the flour, beaten eggs, salt and oil in mixing bowl.
Add enough water to make stiff dough. Roll out very thin; cut in strips and drop into boiling broth that the bouillon has been added.
Reduce heat and cook for approximately 15 minutes, uncovered and without stirring.

title: short cut lasagna
directions: Cook meat, breaking apart.
In a large saucepan mix together tomatoes, tomato sauce, spaghetti mix and V-8 juice.
Bring this mixture to a boil, then add meat and simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with oil and add a layer of the meat sauce into the dish.
Add a layer of uncooked noodles, cottage cheese and mozzarella.
Repeat this until ingredients are used, ending with meat sauce.
Cover with foil; set baking dish into jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove and let cool for 15 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread mix according to directions, cool.
Stir together salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Set aside.
Combine tomatoes and green onions; gently toss.
Crumble half the cornbread into a large salad bowl; top with half of each beans, tomato mixture, cheese, corn, bacon and dressing.
Repeat layers.
Cover and chill. Yield
10 to 12 servings.

title: swedish apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Lightly spray 8 x 8-inch pan or pie plate with Pam and bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Best served warm with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: chicken fried venison
directions: Pound steak with meat mallet on both sides.
Soak in 4 cups milk for one hour.
Mix all dry ingredients in bowl.
Remove steak from milk and put it in a separate bowl.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl at one time.
Pour into 2 regular bread pans.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini crab cakes
directions: Make into patties and deep fry.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add additional mayonnaise, if more moisture is needed.
Serve on lettuce leaves or as a spread for sandwiches.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter in a double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Have two pieces of foil ready and divide mixture onto them.
Wait until cool so it can be worked into a roll, 2 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap the roll in foil.
Chill in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Roll in powdered sugar and slice.
Keep each divided piece in foil.

title: broccoli and raisin salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cheese, raisins, pecans, onion and bacon in large bowl.
Toss gently.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Pour over broccoli mixture; stir and chill before serving.

title: easy beef pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut steak into 1/4-inch thick strips.
In a large skillet, heat oil and add beef; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Remove from skillet.
In the same skillet, add mushrooms, onion, garlic powder and water.
Cook 3 minutes.
Stir in gravy and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Return meat to the skillet.
Stir.
Cut biscuits in half; arrange on top of beef mixture.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix and cook all until thick and smooth.
Just before removing from heat, add 1 teaspoon lemon flavoring and small lump of oleo or butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.

title: oven turkey salad(casserole)
directions: Combine turkey, celery, water chestnuts, mushrooms and pimiento in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Stir gravy mix, milk and mayonnaise together until smooth.
Add seasoned salt.
Add to turkey mixture and stir to coat evenly. Bake in preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with onions and continue baking 3 to 5 minutes or until browned.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook hamburger.
Heat soups.
Add chili sauce and meat.
In a 5-quart casserole dish, pour some mixture and start layering 2 dozen corn tortillas.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese; bake until cheese melts.
Guaranteed to feed an army!

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place eggs in a covered pot and bring to a hard boil.
Turn off heat; do not lift lid or remove from burner.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Cool eggs and halve them.
Remove yolks and mash them until smooth.
Add in mustard, Miracle Whip and about 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Alter the ingredient amounts to your taste.

title: zucchini dish
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, Cheez Whiz and 3/4 stick margarine.
Pour in a casserole dish, then mix Ritz crackers and 3/4 stick of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: black-eyed cornbread
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a skillet over medium heat.
Cook until all pink is gone from beef.
Drain.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Stir until moist.
Stir all ingredients together.
Bake in a 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: choco-cherry ice cream
directions: Combine chocolate milk, sweetened condensed milk, evaporated milk and sugar. Mix well and then stir in chopped maraschino cherries with the reserved juice.
Pour into canister and freeze according to directions with your ice cream freezer.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all together and cook in unbaked pie shell at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Cut each hot dog into 5 pieces. Place all ingredients in frying pan with cover. Cook slowly for 2 hours; stir frequently.

title: fudge icing
directions: Boil all together for 1 minute.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla after cooked.
Cool some, then ice your cake.

title: chili nachos supreme
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium saucepan, heat chili until hot. Spread chips in single layer onto ungreased baking sheet.
Spoon beans over chips; top with chili, cheese and chilies.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with guacamole, if desired.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: bread sticks
directions: Dissolve package of yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon honey.
Mix dry and wet ingredients together; knead briefly.
Roll into thin sticks.
Roll sticks in sesame seeds (optional).
Let rise 10 minutes.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Great fun for kids!

title: gayle's banana split cake
directions: Bake at 350°. Let cake cool.

title: pie crust
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 13 dish; cool.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Dip batter over melted margarine and spoon 1-quart of fruit over batter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion; drain.
Stir in pepper, tomato sauce and catsup; heat.
Alternate meat and cheese slices in a 2-quart casserole.
Arrange canned biscuits around edge of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon cream cheese dessert
directions: Lay 1 package crescent rolls on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread on top of rolls. Unroll and lay second package of crescent rolls on top of cream cheese mixture.
Melt margarine and pour on top.
Sprinkle a cinnamon and sugar mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 greased pie plates. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk, stirring constantly until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water or to 234°.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until nearly stiff. Pour into buttered pan.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and flour.
Add vinegar, water and butter.
Bring to boil; cook until thick.

title: carne con queso
directions: Slice steak thinly.
Cook steak, onions and pepper in butter in frying pan.
After steak is cooked thoroughly add sour cream. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cheese; stir in and cook until cheese is melted.
Add picante sauce if desired.

title: mock pate de foie gras
directions: Simmer giblets in water to cover until tender, about 20 minutes for liver; 1 to 3 hours for gizzard.
Add the salt when almost done.
Cool in the stock.
Grind the giblets or liver to a smooth paste; add butter, seasonings and enough of the stock to make a paste.
Add more seasonings, if desired.
Place in a greased glass bowl and store in the refrigerator.
Tomato catsup may be used for additional seasoning.
Makes 1 cup.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature; beat until fluffy. Gradually add confectioners sugar.
Add melted chocolate, nuts and vanilla.
Press in buttered pan.
Chill at least 30 minutes before cutting.

title: quick fudge(microwave)
directions: Place all ingredients except nuts in a large bowl.
Microwave on Medium (50%) until chocolate chips are melted, 4 to 6 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased square baking dish (8 x 8-inch).

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make a dark brown roux with oil and flour.
Add water; bring to a boil and cook until dissolved.
Reduce heat to medium and add tomatoes with chilies, celery, onions, bell pepper and garlic; chop enough shrimp to make 1 cup and add to gumbo.
Simmer on low heat for 3 hours.
Add remaining shrimp and simmer for 10 minutes. Add crab meat, oysters (and oyster liquid), salt, black pepper and cayenne pepper.
Simmer for another 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice in soup bowls.

title: thick and creamy chewy chocolate cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla. Add flour, soda and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: potato bake
directions: Arrange potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix and pour over soup, sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Spread over grated Cheddar cheese and pat down.
Sprinkle with corn flakes and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple picnic salad
directions: In a bowl, gradually stir undrained pineapple into cream cheese.
Stir in pudding mix.
When it starts to thicken, fold in pineapple chunks and whipped topping.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish. Refrigerate.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.

title: pudding pie
directions: Put banana into crust.
Prepare pudding and milk in small bowl until thick.
Fold half of Cool Whip into pudding.
Pour over the banana; chill until set.
Use remaining Cool Whip and nuts to garnish as desired.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Prepare Minute rice as directed and substitute chicken broth for water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion, cream of chicken soup and chicken pieces to rice.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 25 minutes on 350°.

title: cheese chops
directions: Brown pork chops; drain off grease.
Place chops back in skillet.
Add French onion soup.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 45 minutes or until tender.
When tender, melt 2 pieces of cheese on each chop and serve.

title: bubble bread
directions: Place 24 frozen rolls in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix pudding and brown sugar; sprinkle over rolls.
Add white sugar and cinnamon which have been mixed together.
Sprinkle with nuts. Pour margarine over all.
Let rise in pan overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 15 minutes, then turn pan over onto plate.
(If rolls rise above pan, punch down lightly.)

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, egg yolks and vanilla.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook on medium-high heat until mixture boils. Boil; stir 1 minute.
Line a 10 x 6-inch pan with graham crackers or cookies.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Slowly pour pudding over all.
May cover with more crushed crackers or cookies if desired. Chill.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese with cracker crumbs.
Add liquid from 1 can of asparagus to soup.
Use 1/4 of butter in bottom of casserole dish and the remaining on top.

title: toffee squares
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate). Mix butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Measure flour by sifting. Stir in flour and salt until dough is well blended. Spread in a rectangle about 13 x 10-inch on greased baking sheet, leaving about 1-inch all around edge of baking sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until nicely browned. (For a softer cake-like cookie, spread dough in an oblong pan, 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch; bake 25 to 30 minutes.) Crust will be soft. Remove from oven.

title: strawberry glazed ham
directions: Trim skin from ham.
With sharp knife score fat surface, making uniform diagonal cuts about 1/8 inch deep and 3/4 inch apart.
Place ham fat side up on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Bake in 325° oven for 1 3/4 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Mix baking soda, salt and cornmeal.
Gradually add well beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Heat skillet and grease bottom and sides of skillet with butter.
Pour mixture into heated skillet and place on middle shelf of 400° oven; bake 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour vegetable salad
directions: Combine salt, white vinegar, oil, water and sugar for the marinade.
Boil together for 5 minutes.
Pour over the celery, onions and green pepper.
Allow to cool.
Then add the remainder of the vegetables, which have been drained.
This will keep about 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: annie's alice springs chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts side by side in a well greased baking dish.
Top each breast with one slice of provolone.
Sprinkle bacon pieces over provolone slices evenly.
Uniformly pour entire bottle of salad dressing over each breast to cover bacon and cheese.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve with a slotted spoon.

title: chocolate-bourbon pecan pie
directions: Place pie crust in pie plate and refrigerate.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chocolate and butter in microwave-safe bowl and melt (approximately 1 minute on High).
Add sugar and corn syrup, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Set aside to cool for about 10 minutes.
Add the eggs and bourbon while beating constantly with a whisk until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake on the center rack for 55 to 60 minutes (the surface will have little cracks and be crisp to the touch).

title: chicken breasts with apple stuffing
directions: In a large saucepan bring water, apple juice and 4 tablespoons of butter to a boil.
Remove from heat and add stuffing mix and 2 tablespoons of maple syrup.
Set aside.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix until smooth and pour on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (30 to 40 minutes).
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 12 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat first 4 filling ingredients, then add chocolate chips. Set aside.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix together and store in a tightly closed container.

title: veggie clam sauce and pasta
directions: Saute all veggies in oil.
Add white wine and clams and juice; boil for 5 minutes or until sauce thickens. Serve over angel hair pasta with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine peaches, granulated sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon.
In medium mixing bowl, combine remaining 2/3 cup baking mix with brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is size of small peas.
Stir in milk until mixture is moistened.

title: crab cakes
directions: Brown onion in butter until tender; carefully clean crabmeat and mix with all ingredients except crumbs; form into half a dozen cakes.
Roll in crumbs and fry in oil over medium heat.
Brown on first sides and then turn (about 4 minutes each side).

title: beef and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausages well.
Cut into thirds and place in a 3 or 4-quart casserole dish.
Reserve 2 tablespoons fat from sausages. Brown beef in 1 tablespoon fat; place in casserole dish.
Cook onion and garlic in remaining fat, just until tender.
Add green peppers; cook 1 minute longer, stirring occasionally.
Turn into casserole.
Add potatoes and well drained beans; sprinkle with seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Add bouillon.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Add ingredients and cook at low temperature until thick.
Pour into baked pie shells. Top with meringue and brown in oven.

title: beef stew
directions: Thoroughly brown meat in hot Crisco; add water, lemon, Worcestershire, sliced onions, bay leaves and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Remove bay leaves.
Add vegetables; cover and cook 30 minutes or until done.

title: alabama corn griddle cakes
directions: Combine cornmeal and water in a large mixing bowl; stir well. Set aside for 5 minutes. Gradually add milk to cornmeal mixture, stirring well. Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt; stir into cornmeal mixture. Add beaten eggs and 2 tablespoons melted butter; stir well.

title: helen's honey baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken parts; remove skin, if desired.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Add remaining ingredients, except chicken.
Mix well.
Roll chicken in mixture and arrange in a single layer in same pan.
Bake at 375°, basting occasionally, for 40 minutes (30 minutes if boneless chicken is used).
Serves 4.

title: white liniment
directions: Put in a bottle and shake well.
Rub on aching joints.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Preparation time is 10 minutes.
Cooking Time is 1 hour.
tags: Campbell's condensed new cream of chicken

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in a large saucepan and heat just until sugar is completely dissolved.
Stir in peanut butter and corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool completely or place in greased baking dish and let cool and cut into squares.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: shake 'n bake coating for chicken
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Put in jar with tight fitting lid and store in refrigerator.
When ready to use, take out needed amount.
Dip chicken in milk or club soda, then in coating.
Bake in pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until tender.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix everything together and make balls.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook in greased 9-inch skillet at 450° until golden brown.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter; add onions, garlic and mushrooms, cook until onions are transparent; remove.
Fry steak in same pan until brown. Remove meat.
Make sauce in pan with salt and flour.
Add bouillon and sour cream, stir until thick on medium heat.
Add worcestershire sauce and kitchen bouquet.
Serve on bed of egg noodles or rice.

title: strawberry sundae(serves 1)
directions: Place sliced strawberries in bowl and sprinkle with diet sweetener.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Place lettuce leaf on plate; layer with peach slices and cottage cheese.
Top with strawberries.

title: halibut fajitas
directions: Optional Ingredients:
Salsa, sour cream, diced tomatoes, grated cheese, refried beans, lime wedges and guacamole.

title: chicken curry stew
directions: Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in butter. Add onion, parsley and garlic.
Cook until onion is soft.
Add tomatoes, curry and remaining spices.
Cover.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
Add raisins; simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: ice cream cookie sandwich
directions: Line bottom of one 9-inch round cake pan with aluminum foil. Spread ice cream in pan.
Return to freezer until firm.
Run knife around edge of pan to loosen ice cream.
Remove from pan and wrap in foil.
Return to freezer.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
This recipe will make 1 large or 2 medium balls.
Form ball with your hands and roll onto a plate that has finely chopped walnuts or pecans. Cover with foil and refrigerate.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Keeps 2 weeks.
Make 1 day ahead.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Heat 6 cups of sugar and 4 cups cider vinegar for sauce.
Mix 1 cup flour and 1 cup vinegar and add to heated vinegar and sugar so as not to lump.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 teaspoon turmeric, 2 teaspoons dry mustard and 2 teaspoons mustard seed.
Add vegetables and bring to a boil.

title: fruit balls
directions: Cook oleo,
coconut, dates and brown sugar until blended. Cool
minutes.	Add
Rice
Krispies and chopped nuts. Roll into balls and shake in bag of powdered sugar.

title: sausage balls
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and squish together.
Pinch off little balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, water, vanilla and peanut butter.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Press with floured fork. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Blend cream cheese add all other ingredients mix well. Cover and chill.

title: oven barbecued beef brisket
directions: Mix liquid smoke, Worcestershire sauce and salts together. Pierce top of brisket in several places.
Sprinkle liquid smoke mixture over brisket.
Wrap brisket in an airtight foil envelope leaving some air space between foil and brisket on top and sides. Place in a dripper pan and refrigerate 24 hours.
Take brisket directly from fridge to oven (preheated to 275°).
Cook for 5 hours.
Open foil and pour barbecue sauce on top of the brisket. Close foil and bake brisket 2 hours longer or until it is fork-tender.
Cut brisket in slices across the grain.
Skim off excess fat from drippings and discard.
Serve brisket slices with sauce to be spooned over them.
Great reheated in sauce!

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in large punch bowl.
Add more orange juice and 7-Up to taste.
Add ice cream to taste.
Add more or less of all ingredients, depending on size of party.

title: grandmother's marshmallow treats
directions: Melt marshmallows with margarine in large saucepan over low heat; stirring until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using greased spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into greased 13x9x2-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Take one cup friendship and 1 cup thoughtfulness.
Mix well with a pinch of powdered tenderness lightly beaten into a bowl of loyalty to which has been added 1 cup faith, 1 cup hope and 1 cup of charity.
Be sure to add a teaspoon of gaiety that sings and the ability to laugh at little things.
Moisten with tears and sympathy.
Bake in a good natured pan.
Serve often.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Also brush top with extra Heinz 57 if desired.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water.
Remove and debone.
Save broth. Cook broccoli for 5 minutes in broth.
Line broccoli on side of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with stems in and leaves out.
Place chicken on stems.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Pour over chicken, leaving broccoli flowerets uncovered.
Sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Put bread crumbs over cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: taco pizza
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Press on medium size plate or tray, cover cream cheese with taco sauce.
Sprinkle green peppers and onions over sauce.
Put Mozzarella cheese or American cheese over the top.
Cut olives in slices and put over the top.

title: tossed italian salad
directions: Salad:
Place spinach, lettuce, pepper strips, radish slices and onion rings in a large salad bowl and toss lightly.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Put rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle Jell-O over rhubarb. Sprinkle sugar over.
Put 3 cups of small marshmallows on top.
Pour cake batter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smores cheesecake squares
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Mix well. Measure out one cup and set aside. Press remainder of crumbs into a 9x13 baking pan. Combine next 4
ingredients in mixing bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy. Fold in half of chocolate chips. Pour into prepared crust. Sprinkle

mini marshmallows over filling and sprinkle with rest of chocolate chips. Sprinkle reserved crust crumbs over all. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until center is set. Cool. Chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Blend potatoes, soup, milk, sour cream, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Pat mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay browned pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven; sprinkle top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix eggs, milk, oil and water.
Add cake mix and pudding; mix well.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes while slowly adding sugar. Blend in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients and carefully fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread into well greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and at once turn out on a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Start at narrow end and roll towel and cake up together.
Cool completely; unroll and fill with filling.

title: turnovers
directions: For sour milk, add 1 tablespoon ReaLemon or vinegar to sweet milk.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir water in gradually.
Stir over medium heat, bringing mixture to boil.
Boil and stir 1 minute more.
Take off heat.
Stir about half of mixture into egg yolks, then return to saucepan.
Mix well. Return to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute more and take off heat.
Stir in lemon juice, butter and rind. Pour into baked shell.
Turn oven to 400°.

title: fudge cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add water, shortening and vanilla.
Beat with a mixer on low speed to medium speed until combined.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and melted chocolate.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8 x 1 1/2-inch or 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pans.
Cool thoroughly on wire racks.
Makes 12 servings.

title: two tone fudge
directions: Combine brown sugar, granulated sugar and butter in a large, heavy saucepan.
Bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and Marshmallow Creme. Stir until it has melted and mixture is smooth.
Into 2 cups of hot mixture, add butterscotch morsels and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts. Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Spread evenly into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
To remaining mixture, add chocolate morsels and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Spread evenly over butterscotch mixture.
Chill.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sour cream, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Put on whatever topping you like.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients, except chips, and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips on top.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs and wings
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer together for 20 minutes. Pour sauce over UNCOOKED ribs OR over FRIED chicken drumettes. Bake in 250° oven in a covered pan.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Stir the first 4 ingredients together with a fork until crumbly. Press into a lightly greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: peanut blossoms(cookies)
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter and both sugars. Add egg and vanilla.
Beat together.
Add flour, soda and salt. Mix thoroughly.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Then place chocolate candy kiss on top of each one, return to oven and bake another 5 minutes or until brown.
Cool!

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Then add flour; dough will be soft.
Spoon in muffin tins 1/3 full.
Bake at 400° for approximately 15 to 17 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Pour into well greased loaf pan.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: white grape juice punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl.
Chill with ice ring made of frozen juice and fruit.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in large baking pan.
Bake 1/2 hour in moderate oven (350°).
If desired, cut in serving size portions first.
Brown onions in fat; add lemon juice, vinegar, Worcestershire, Tabasco, brown sugar, water, chili sauce and salt. Simmer slowly for 20 minutes; pour over spareribs.
Bake spareribs 1 hour longer, basting ribs occasionally.
Serves four.

title: denver sandwich for one
directions: Combine egg, ham, milk, onion powder and basil; beat well. Melt margarine.
Add pepper; cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Reduce heat. Add egg mixture, cooking until set.
Place tomato slice on each muffin half; top each with egg mixture.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in an 8-inch square pan.
Combine other ingredients until mixture is like coarse meal.
Sprinkle this over peaches and bake, uncovered, at 400° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and mushrooms.
Wash spinach; drain. Layer spinach, meat and cheese like a lasagne, then top with bread crumbs and eggs, mixed.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend until smooth. Serve with fruit.

title: clam canapes
directions: Blend cheese and butter with fork.
Add clams, onions and salt.
Toast bread on one side.
Spread mixture on untoasted side. Put in oven at 325°.
Serve when hot and bubbly.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Will keep indefinitely in the refrigerator.

title: fish with rice
directions: Brown onions in oil to a rich brown.
Strain (reserve oil and onions).
Bring water to a boil; drop onions in water and add all seasonings.
Cut fish in pieces and drop fish in water (onion water).
Bring to a boil, then reduce to medium fire and cook fish about 20 minutes.
Take fish out of seasoned water; put in dish to cool.
Strain water; bring to a boil; add rice (add water, if needed).
Cook covered on medium to low fire until rice is done. When almost done, add oil (onion was fried in).
Fold into rice easy.
Cover rice; turn fire off and let finish cooking.
Meantime, bone and flake fish (be sure fish is well drained).
Brown pine nuts in butter; drain and set aside.
When rice is done, spread on a platter.
Spread flaked fish over rice and sprinkle pine nuts over all.
If no pine nuts, use walnuts (do not fry, just heat).

title: italian pot roast
directions: Trim roast of all visible fat.
Place in crock-pot.
Sprinkle other dry ingredients over meat.
Add water.
Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours.
Turn off and let sit for 1/2 hour.
(Roast will absorb liquid.)
Shred meat with wire whisk and serve on "sub" rolls with cheese.
Also good over buttered noodles or rice.

title: low-fat cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients and chill in fridge until firm.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except for cheese and chips.
Top with grated cheese and chips.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 450° oven.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and add onions, green pepper and celery.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and salad oil in a shaker and shake well. Pour dressing over vegetables and let stand covered in refrigerator overnight.
This makes a good sized salad which keeps without getting soggy.
The sweet-sour dressing is a tangy contrast to the mild beans.

title: banana guava cake
directions: Stir the bananas, applesauce and guava nectar together.
You may use an electric mixer for this recipe, but it is not necessary. Stir the dry ingredients together, then stir them into the liquid mixture, stirring until the flour is thoroughly moistened.
Pour the mixture into a 13 x 22-inch cake pan that has been sprayed with Pam and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
tags: Hawaiian Sun frozen guava nectar base

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Sift the flour, adding the sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Add the water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Fill cupcake liners with 1/3 batter. Add spoonful cream cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crunchy lemon chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cereal, salt and lemon peel.
Dip chicken in egg white.
Coat chicken with cereal mixture.
Arrange in 13 x 9-inch baking pan which has been sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Bake 50 minutes or until cooked through.

title: mound bars
directions: Blend cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into a 10 x 10-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle coconut over mixture. Pour condensed milk over coconut.
Bake for 15 minutes. Remove from oven again. Top with chocolate chips and bake briefly to spread chips.
Refrigerate until well set.
Cut into squares.

title: hungarian cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook noodles 8 minutes in boiling water.
Drain.
Melt oleo in large skillet; saute chopped onion and cabbage until cabbage is tender.
Add salt and pepper seasoning.
Mix together with noodles in casserole.

title: white veal scaloppine
directions: Dust cutlets with the 1/4 cup flour, shaking off excess.
Heat oil and 1 tablespoon of the butter in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.
When fat is hot, add veal in a single layer, without crowding and cook until browned on both sides (about 1 to 2 minutes on each side).
Remove from pan and set aside.

title: greek shrimp and penne pasta
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in saucepan.
Add garlic and cook for 1 minute.
Add wine, salt and pepper, basil and oregano and cook at a gentle simmer for 10 minutes.
Heat remaining 3 tablespoons olive oil in skillet.
Add shrimp and cook until they turn pink.
Add dash of hot pepper and stir.
Spoon shrimp and pan juices into small baking pan.
Sprinkle with Feta cheese.
Spoon tomato sauce over.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cook pasta while baking.
Drain pasta; place in shallow dish and spoon shrimp and sauces over.
Serve with bread and salad.
Enjoy!

title: garlic-paprika chicken
directions: Combine flour, garlic powder, paprika and parsley.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Fry in salad oil until tender.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: An all-ready pie crust works fine (graham cracker or chocolate).

title: noella's pancake
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into 8-inch pie pan.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: 1-2-3 stew
directions: Place meat in pan.
Mix water and soups together.
Pour over the meat. Cover and place in 300° oven for 3 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Mix white wine, salt, 1 green onion and ginger and rub chicken. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Make sauce out of remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 12 to 20 minutes more.
Serve over rice.
Good served with hot and sour cabbage as side dish.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix cream cheese and margarine until smooth and fluffy.
Add vanilla and sugar and mix until smooth.

title: mexican cheese chicken
directions: Chop cooked chicken into bite-sized pieces. Layer in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Add chopped onion and cheeses. Mix liquids with mixer. Pour over dry ingredients. Work with a spoon so liquids can go to the bottom. If mixture is dry, you may add another can of cream of mushroom soup. Bake for 35 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: moon cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to boil.
Add 1 cup flour and stir rapidly until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool a bit. Add eggs one at a time and beat until shiny.
Spread on 11 x 15-inch ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Cool completely and do not prick cake.
Make pudding following package directions.
Add softened cream cheese to pudding.
Spread on crust.
Refrigerate 20 minutes.
Top with whipped topping and nuts.

title: black bean pizza
directions: Place pizza shell on pizza pan that has been sprayed with Pam and sprinkled with cornmeal (this makes it easy to cut and serve). Spread drained black beans on shell, then salsa.
Sprinkle on cooked turkey sausage.
Cover with cheese and cilantro.
Bake at 400° in preheated oven for 7 minutes.
Serve with a large green salad, using nonfat Italian dressing.

title: chicken dumplings
