directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until tender.
Remove chicken from pot, let cool and debone.
Bring broth to a boil and drop in tortilla strips.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes slow and put deboned chicken in pot.
Cook slow with cover on pot for 5 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients, adding pecans last.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: aunt verlie's banana bread
directions: Put in a large bowl the vegetable oil, sugar, eggs, bananas, milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder into wet mixture.
Stir thoroughly.
Add walnuts. Place in a greased bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine graham crackers, oleo and powdered sugar.
Mix well and line pan with the crumbs, reserving a few for the top.

title: jim-jam cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll thin and cut out. Bake at 375° until a little brown. Stick together with jam.

title: easy does it quiche
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed on box.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan, forming a crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: chicken fingers with honey mustard
directions: Cut chicken into strips 1/2x2-inch.
Mix flour salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in milk.
Roll in flour mixture coating well. Place chicken on waxed paper.
Heat oil in skillet until 350°. Place chicken in oil evenly, turn, cook chicken about 3 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towel.

title: ripe banana muffins
directions: Mix bananas, shortening, sugar and salt; add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Sift and add flour, baking soda and baking powder. Beat and mix in nuts.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: martha's carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, carrots and vanilla. Mix in dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening with molasses.
Beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour milk to creamed mixture.
Pour into well greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350 F for 50-60 minutes.

title: geri's zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until thick and lemon colored.
Mix in next 5 ingredients and fold in walnuts.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured 8-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pans 10 minutes and then turn out on racks.

title: aviation club dip
directions: Blend mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill for 1 hour.

title: louisiana pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat after each one is added.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix dry mixture to creamy mixture with milk a little at a time until all is creamy.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done (do not overcook).

title: mexican steak
directions: Brown steak with onions and garlic.
Add Tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder.
Cook on medium heat about 1 hour or until steak is tender.
Add remaining spices, add beans just to heat. Serve with flour tortillas.

title: calico meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy in a small deep bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar to make a stiff meringue. Fold in M&M's (plain chocolate ones).
Grease and flour a large cookie sheet.
Drop meringue mixture by teaspoons on cookie sheet. Garnish each with an M&M.
Bake in slow oven at 250° for 30 minutes or until cookie is firm to the touch but still white. Cool cookies on cookie sheet on wire rack.
Remove from sheet with spatula.
Store in tightly covered containers.
Do not try to make during humid weather.

title: orange baked fish
directions: Grease baking dish and arrange fillets skin side down. Sprinkle ingredients evenly over fish.
Cover and chill 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in large boiler; bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes, stirring all the time.
Cake layer must be ready when icing is finished or icing will get too hard to spread if not put on cake immediately.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli; omit salt.
Blend eggs, soup and cheese; add mayonnaise and milk.
Stir in broccoli.
Melt butter; toss with 1 cup bread crumbs.
Top broccoli with crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour until lightly browned or bubbly.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Note:
This cake should be made in a large flat pan that it can be left in until served.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl mix flour, sugar, eggs, salt, baking soda and sour cream; mix well.
In saucepan bring to boil
butter, water and cocoa, stirring frequently.
While hot add to first mixture; mix well. Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Bake exactly 20 minutes.
Mix frosting last 5 minutes while cake is baking.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Parboil chicken 25 minutes or until tender.
Remove from bones.
Place cut-up chicken in lightly buttered oblong baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Toss crumbs and oleo together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: leek soup
directions: Cut leeks into short (1-inch) pieces.
Saute them in butter. When they are golden brown, add water and potatoes.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are soft.
Remove potatoes and mash them; then, return them to the soup.
Add the cream.
Serve over slices of bread lightly sauteed in butter.
Top with grated Swiss cheese.
(For those watching fat intake, substitute milk for cream and toast the bread without butter.)

title: blackberry and apple cordial
directions: Put blackberries into a large saucepan with the apple juice. Bring to a boil; simmer over very low heat for 20 minutes, or until the fruit is soft.
Mash with a potato masher.
Line a plastic sieve with a double layer of cheesecloth.
Strain the juice through a plastic bowl.
Gather the corners of the cheesecloth and lightly squeeze to extract all the juice possible. Measure the juice.

title: lipton pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into thin strips, 2 inches long.
In large skillet, brown meat in oil; turn frequently.
Stir in soup mix and 2 cups water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in peppers.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, or until tender.
Blend cornstarch with 1/2 cup water and stir into skillet.
Cook while stirring until thickened. Add a bit of soy sauce when browning meat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine applesauce and powdered pectin in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Add cinnamon oil, red food coloring and sugar.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pour into scalded jars or glasses.
Seal.

title: wonton cookies
directions: Work with 3 wrappers at a time, one on top of the other.
Cut in half.
Make a 1-inch slit lengthwise in center of each half and pull one end up and through the slit to make a loose bow.
Pour oil to a depth of 4 inches in a deep saucepan or Grandpappy fryer. Being careful not to overcrowd, deep fry bows until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper toweling and sprinkle with cinnamon and powdered sugar.

title: quesadillas
directions: Spread butter on tortillas.
Toast in 350° oven for 5 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on toasted tortillas.
Bake at 400° until cheese bubbles.
Cut into wedges.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix with a spoon.
Mix dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture.
Add nuts and dates.
Grease and flour two loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: joyce's chicken
directions: Place butter in baking dish.
Flour chicken and place skin side down.
Bake for 1 hour at 425°.

title: crabmeat yummies(must prepare partially ahead)
directions: Drop mushrooms (preferably sliced) into boiling water for 1 or 2 minutes.
Drain.
Seal in an airtight container or bag.
Then freeze until ready to use.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and melted margarine.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate with back of tablespoon, forming sides and lip on edge of plate.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Parboil zucchini for about 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out zucchini pulp, leaving shell.
Place zucchini, cut side down, to drain.
Chop pulp.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine
graham
cracker
crumbs with melted margarine. Press into
a 9 x 11-inch dish.
With electric mixer beat egg whites, 1/2 cup margarine and powdered sugar.
Spread on crumb mixture. Layer
the	sliced bananas and then pineapple on top of
second layer.
Cover
with
Cool
Whip.
Spread
chopped cherries	and pecans on top.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine soup mix and cold water. Beat with whisk to remove lumps.
Bring to a boil, partially covered, and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and stir in cheese until completely melted.
May add 2 cups chopped, cooked chicken.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Cook for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 pie.
Double for 2 pies.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream, soup, onion and 1/2 melted butter, cheese, salt and pepper. Put in glass dish (spray with nonstick spray).
Top with remaining butter and crushed corn flakes.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cracker crumb crust
directions: Spray 9-inch pie dish with Pam.
Combine crackers, crumbs, sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Gradually add Butter Buds.
Press into bottom and sides of pie dish.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Use a large 9 x 13-inch pan or large tube pan.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Reserve 1/2 chow mein noodles.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine the remaining noodles with the seven other ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Add reserved noodles on top.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: snow white cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add oleo, milk, tuna and soup.
Cube cheese and add.
Place in a casserole dish.
Cook in microwave for a few minutes until cheese is melted or bake in oven in a covered dish for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Use any of the following: broccoli, cauliflower, celery, carrots, green onions, green pepper, red bell pepper, fresh mushrooms.

title: coolrise sweet dough
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, undissolved yeast, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Stir well to blend.
Add softened margarine.
Add hot water to bowl, all at once.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl.
Add eggs and 1 cup more flour.
Beat with mixer at high for 1 minute or until thick and elastic.
Add enough remaining flour until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Cover and let rest 20 minutes. Punch down.
Shape and refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
To bake, remove from refrigerator.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add milk and cream of tartar.
Add corn syrup and cook until soft ball stage is reached.
Remove from heat, then add butter and vanilla.
Let cool.
Beat until creamy. Use on your favorite cake.

title: beef burgundy(good with pop overs)
directions: Cook and stir beef in shortening in dutch oven until beef is brown. Mix flour, salt, marjoram, thyme, and pepper. Coat beef with four mixture. Heat beef and remaining ingredients to boiling in dutch oven: reduce heat. Cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 1 1/4 hours. Stir in 2 to 3 tsp. browning sauce if desired. You can put this over noodles or beside potatoes.

title: pepper roast
directions: Rub roast with olive oil, garlic and rosemary. Press coarse ground black pepper all over roast (heavy) with palm of hand. Cover loosely with foil or Saran Wrap and let stand for a couple of hours, preferably overnight but not necessary. Bake for 2 hours or until meat thermometer reaches 130°. Cool slightly before slicing.

title: onion crispy chicken
directions: In shallow bowl, combine the butter, worcestershire sauce, mustard, garlic salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in batter mixture, then coat with onions.
Place in greased 9-inch square baking pan, top with remaining onions.
Drizzle with any remaining butter mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken juice runs clear.
Yields 4 servings.

title: veggies and noodles
directions: Saute onions, carrots, green pepper and celery in oil. Do not season!
Add noodles and undiluted soup to veggies.
Mix it all together.

title: ina's smothered chicken breasts
directions: Place a chicken breast on a slice of chipped beef and wrap this in a slice of bacon.
Place meat in a baking pan and pour the mixture of soup and sour cream over all.
(Sprinkle almonds on top if desired.)
Cover.
Bake for 4 hours at 250°.
Serves 8.

title: italian arm roast
directions: Cook in crock pot on low heat for approximately 8 hours. Shred meat and mix with drippings.
Serve on French buns.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all these together and bake at 350° until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes before mixing.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine and add all other ingredients except 1/4 cup margarine and crushed corn flakes.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine and toss with crushed corn flakes.

title: tea cakes(1930)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and blend in flour and salt. Add vanilla and stir well.

title: quick crab dip(heart healthy)
directions: Spread cheese over pan; spread sauce over cheese, leaving a 1-inch plain cheese edge all around.
Shred crab meat generously on top.
Use as a dip with crackers.
Serve as is or garnish with chives, etc.

title: peanut popcorn bars
directions: Combine sugar and corn	syrup.	Bring
to
a full boil. Remove from heat and
stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir quickly until smooth.
Pour
over
popcorn mixed with peanuts. Stir to coat all
particles.
Pat
mixture	firmly into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool;	then cut into 2-inch squares. Makes 16.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 1-3/4 quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered. Serve hot. Good warmed over, too.

title: jean's chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: diabetic dessert - peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls, using about 1 teaspoon of dough for each.
Place 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets; flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 42 cookies.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Mix altogether, saving some of onion to put on top.
Put in greased casserole; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onion; return to oven for 10 more minutes.

title: cheesy chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bits over hot, not boiling, water.
Cool slightly.
Stir cream cheese to soften; blend in 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Chill mixture until thick, then beat until smooth.

title: beef and biscuit bake
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine all other ingredients except biscuits and cheese.
Line a greased baking dish with biscuits. Cover with beef mixture.
Layer biscuits on top of mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until brown.

title: aunt irene's corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole dish for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese balls
directions: Use half the American cheese, half the hot pepper cheese and one 8 ounce cream cheese to each cheese ball.
Mix in spices and season to your own taste.
Place chopped nuts on plastic wrap. Make cheese into 2 balls and roll in the chopped nuts.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for a little while to chill.
Good with snack crackers or by itself if you like cheese.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cake, drain fruits, except cherry pie filling. Prepare pudding mix according to directions.

title: western spoon bread
directions: Combine green pepper, instant onion and tomatoes in mixing bowl.
Let stand 4 or 5 minutes.
Stir in cornmeal, egg, chili con carne seasoning powder, soda, salt and cheese.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into a well-buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until firm.
Spoon out onto plate and serve hot, either plain or with butter.
Makes 8 servings.

title: caramel pie
directions: Pour condensed milk into a 1-quart slow cooker.
Cook, covered, 6 to 7 hours or until mixture is the color of peanut butter, stirring with a wire whisk every 30 minutes.
Pour into pie crust; cool.
Spread whipped topping over top of pie and sprinkle evenly with chopped candy bar.
Cover and chill.
Yield: 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: chess cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; press in buttered pan.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed until thick and lemon colored.
Add butter and next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: orange slice fruit cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mix.
Place flour in a large bowl. Add dates, orange candy and nuts.
Stir to coat each piece.
Add this and the coconut to the creamed mix.
Mix with hands.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 250°.

title: brown sugar french toast
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat. Oil 9 x 13 baking dish. Pour brown sugar mixture into dish and place bread on top. Beat eggs; add vanilla and milk. Pour over bread. Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil.
Add onions and saute for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally until cubes dissolve.
Gradually add noodles and salt so that bouillon mixture continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook. Add milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Makes 12 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan. While cake is baking, simmer pineapple and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
When cake is done, punch holes with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour on pineapple and cool.
Mix pudding and coconut and sprinkle on cake.
Then spread on Cool Whip and sprinkle on chopped nuts.

title: date roll candy
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and butter.
Boil 5 minutes; add dates. Cook until creamy.
Test firm ball in cold water.
Beat and add cherries and nuts.
Pour on wax paper or roll in damp cloth.
Cut when cool.

title: mounds cake
directions: Make chocolate cake in long cake pan.
Cut into two layers with a string when cool.

title: red yam flan
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Scrub the yams and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on size, until they are soft.
Remove them from the oven.
Peel, cut into chunks and puree in blender or food processor.
You should have 1 1/2 cups; set aside to cool.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring by hand.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in long greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put all together and mix dough until dough comes away from side of bowl.
Do in mixer.
Let rise until double in size.
Roll out and cut into rolls.
Let rise again until almost double in size.
If bubbles form, it was too long.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush with melted butter when removed from oven.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Place in shallow baking dish. Lightly mix together bread cubes, onion, butter, 1/4 cup water and garlic salt.
Place a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend soup and 1/3 cup of water; pour over chops and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: tomato soup
directions: In 4-quart pan, heat tomato juice and spices until boiling (stir often).
Mix cornstarch and milk together; pour into soup. Stir and cook until boiling again. Boil for 1 minute.

title: nell schneider's prune cake
directions: Pour boiling water over cut-up prunes.
Let stand 1 hour. Heat oven to desired temperature, depending on pan used.
Grease and flour pan.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soups with sour cream and set aside 1 cup of mixture for topping. Mix the rest of the ingredients (except tortillas) with the remaining soup mixture, reserving 1/2 cup cheese for the topping. Spoon the mixture into the tortillas and roll up. Place seam side down in 9 by 13 inch pan. Pour remaining soup mixture over the top and sprinkle with the remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Great served with a salad and breadsticks.

title: orange glaze spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into 2 rib sections and parboil for 40 minutes. Drain and season with salt and pepper.
Combine all other ingredients and brush on both sides of ribs.
Grill or broil 6 inches from heat source until ribs are hot, about 6 to 7 minutes per side, brushing frequently with sauce.

title: chocolate candy crunch delight
directions: Bake German chocolate cake as directed on box in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool for 30 minutes.
Poke holes all over cake with the end of a wooden spoon.
Pour can of milk all over cake (in all holes) and the same with the caramel topping.
Put Heath bars in big Ziploc baggie and crunch up with hammer.
Cover the whole cake and all the holes.
(You don't want to see any holes.
Should look like Heath bars are just a topping.) Best to make the night before serving.

title: apple crumble
directions: Put sliced apples in a greased dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add flour and salt; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture on top of fruit.
Bake at 375° approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peachy smoothie
directions: Combine the yogurt and nectar in a blender. Add the raspberries and peaches. Blend until smooth.

title: red punch drink
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, orange juice and lemonade as directed on package.
Mix all with pineapple juice.
Pour over ice.

title: christmas roll
directions: Boil milk and sugar until soft ball.
Add dates and cook until hard ball.
Add chopped nuts and stir until stiff.
Roll in ground nuts; chill and slice.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion; drain.
Add sauce, peppers, seasoning and soup.
Stir and let simmer for 20 minutes.

title: ever ready bran muffins
directions: Pour water over Bran Buds.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs. Sift flour, salt and soda.
Mix all together.
Stir until moistened; keep in covered container for up to a month in refrigerator.
May add raisins or nuts or dates.
Bake in muffin tin at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Freeze the canned fruit juices in their cans.
Chill the sodas.
About 3 hours before party, take cans out of the freezer. Empty the frozen slushy juices in punch bowl.
Add the soda. Serves 40.

title: pasta de shuto
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage and beef.
Drain off fat.
Add vegetables and saute just until crisp and tender.
Stir in soups, tomato sauce and spices.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Crumble ingredients together.
Press in 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut in pan.
Mix cake per recipe on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Spread over cake mix and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: potatoes with onion soup
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes (do not peel).
Slice 1/4-inch thick. Melt margarine and mix with onion soup mix, salt and water.
In a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole, put a layer of potatoes, then a layer of onion soup mixture.
Repeat until all has been used.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° (uncovered).

title: lobster stew
directions: Saute lobster meat in butter for approximately 10 minutes. Add sherry, cream and milk.
Blend together.

title: corn chowder
directions: Bring potatoes, water and onion to a boil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice, until potatoes are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes for flavor to develop.
You may add crumbled bacon, ham bits or seafood.

title: b and c casserole
directions: Mix all veggies, cheese, salt and soup in casserole dish.
Top with bred crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until veggies are tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sour cream, cinnamon, vanilla, nuts, bananas and sifted flour.
Mix and pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage corn chowder
directions: Cut sausage into rounds and flatten by hand. Brown in large stockpot. When sausage is done, remove from drippings and set aside.

title: cookies 'n cream ice cream
directions: Mix half and half with eggs and scald. When cool, add sugar, salt and vanilla. Stir in cookies after ice cream is frozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Put salmon in bowl, flake and remove bones.
Beat egg. Combine with milk, crumbs and other ingredients.
Add to salmon. Mix well.
Shape into 6 cakes.
Place in hot shortening over medium heat and brown on both sides.
Serve with tartar sauce, if desired.
These may also be baked at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: luscious lumps
directions: Blend butter, powdered sugar, cornstarch and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Put on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 10 to 13 minutes.

title: hash
directions: Cook a lean beef roast and a lean pork roast in water until meat is very tender.
The meat mixture should be 1/4 pork and 3/4 beef.
Chop meat.
To season meat, use dry onion soup mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Use water in which roasts were cooked to make hash the right consistency.
(The amount of onion soup is a guess, it depends on the amount of meat used; just taste and adjust as you like.)

title: "monkey toes"
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Melt together butter and brown sugar.
Cut rolls into quarters and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Put sugared, quartered rolls in greased Bundt pan. Pour remaining cinnamon and sugar mixture over rolls.
Pour melted butter and brown sugar mixture over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert onto plate and cool.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Break cornbread into pieces and crumble in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Break toast into small pieces and mix with cornbread.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour broth over all.
Mix thoroughly.
Salt to taste.
Also, add sage and black pepper, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: apricot-orange jello salad
directions: Fix jello with 2 cups hot water and 1 cup of juice.
Add fruit and put marshmallows on top.
Chill until set.

title: chili-hominy casserole
directions: Combine 1 cup cheese and remaining ingredients; stir well. Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese salad
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, pineapple and salt and pour over one box lemon jello.
Let stand until slightly jelled.
Add Cheddar cheese and whipping cream.
Don't let the vinegar fool you.
This is a delicious salad.
Can be served with any meal.

title: pizza hot dish(makes 10 servings)
directions: Brown meat, drain off fat.
Combine meat, green pepper, onion and spices with tomato sauce; simmer about 15 minutes over low heat.
Cook noodles; drain.
Place noodles in bottom of 9 x 13-inch nonstick pan sprayed with release agent.

title: overnight chicken
directions: Make soupy.
Mix together; pour in glass baking dish.
Cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together; mix buttermilk and flavorings together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk mixture to sugar/shortening mixture and beat well after each addition.
Pour in greased and floured large Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool about 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cream margarine, eggs and sweetener.
Add soda, spices, flour and applesauce or bananas; mix well.
Fold in fruits and nuts. Bake
in
loaf
pan at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.
When done, let stand in pan 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mrs. grabin's eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplants and cut into cubes.
Boil in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Cook chopped onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add to eggplant.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 1/2 cups hot water, then pour over cooked rice.
Let stand 10 minutes. Add 2 whole eggs to eggplant mixture.
After letting rice set, add to eggplant mixture.
Put in greased baking dish.
Top with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake until eggs are done.

title: jonelle's angel hair
directions: Cook fresh broccoli until tender.
Sit aside.
In a small saucepan, add olive oil, butter and garlic.
Simmer until garlic is tender.
Cook pasta 2 minutes or as directed.
Mix all together and add cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Brown onion in butter.
Mix eggs, milk, crumbled up bread, cream of mushroom soup, onion and squash. Pour into casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes, then at 350° for 10 more minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix ground beef with onion and 1/2 cup water.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Drain fat from casserole.
Spread mashed potatoes over meat.
Return to oven and bake until heated through, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ice cream puffs
directions: In a small saucepan, bring to a boil the water, butter, salt and sugar.

Add all at once the flour and cook the paste over a low heat, beating it briskly and constantly until the ingredients are thoroughly combined and the mixture clearly leaves the sides of the pan and forms a ball.
Remove pan from heat and beat in the eggs one at a time.
(If eggs are unusually small, use an extra one.) Drop tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 to 18 minutes.
Reduce oven to 375° and bake until golden brown and feels light in the hand.
If puffs brown too quickly, cover with a piece of paper.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix well and put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pies(2 pies, no crust)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and flour; beat well.
Add coconut. Pour into lightly greased 9-inch glass pie plates.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and pie won't shake, around 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except half of the potato chips.
Place in a baking dish. Top with remaining chips, lightly crushed.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: a true margarita
directions: Combine tequila, Triple Sec and lime juice.
Shake with ice and strain into glass.
Garnish with lime slice.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, mixing well. On foil or wax paper, pat meat into 12 x 10 rectangle. Arrange ham slices on meat. Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese over ham. Start from short end and roll up, using foil to lift. Seal edges and ends so cheese won't cook out. Place roll seam side down in 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: frozen cream cheese salad or heavenly hash
directions: Partly drain pineapple.
Add marshmallows and let stand 1 hour. Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold into whipped cream. Fold in fruit and marshmallow mixture.
Freeze.
Makes 16 small molds.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Saute onions and tomatoes in oil until soft.
In a large bowl, mix tomato and onion mixture with the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a baking dish and bake in a 400° oven until bubbly and browned.
Serve with taco chips.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and let cool.
Remove skin and bones and cut into bite size chunks.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in skillet; add chopped onion and celery.
Cook over low heat until tender.
Break bread into small pieces and add hot chicken broth until bread is soaked.
Fold in chicken, onion, celery and diced eggs.
Place in 8 x 8-inch dish, uncovered; sprinkle with pepper and salt.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate candy balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, milk, butter and pecans together.
Put in refrigerator for 2 or 3 hours.
Take out and roll into balls.
Mix the paraffin wax and chocolate in boiler; cook on low heat and stir constantly until melted.
Dip balls in hot chocolate mixture. Let stand on waxed paper until hardened.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in buttered baking dish.
Cover each breast with one slice of cheese.
In small saucepan, mix 2 tablespoons butter with flour; blend over low heat until smooth and bubbling.
Slowly stir in milk and broth; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add wine and pour over chicken.
Combine stuffing mix with remaining 3 tablespoons butter.
Spread over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: garlic cheese biscuit
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Stir baking mix, cheese and milk together to form a soft dough. Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Stir melted butter and garlic powder together and brush over hot biscuits. Makes 9 to 10 biscuits.

title: white cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Last, add beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Bake at 350°.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Cut corn from cob, scraping cob well.
Place corn and scrapings in a large saucepan.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Do not drain.
Place corn in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt and eggs.
Stir in milk.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Serves 8.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugars, dressing and vanilla with mixer; add flour and baking soda.
Set aside 1 cup of the batter.
Spread remaining batter into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with milk over low heat.
Top crust with caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with chips and pecans.
Spoon reserved 1 cup batter by teaspoon over pecans.
Continue baking 12 to 15 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 11 x 16 pan. Cover bottom of pan with coconut, as much as you desire. Cover coconut with chopped nuts. Prepare cake as directed on box and pour over coconut and nut mixture. Combine margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese. Stir until smooth. Spoon over cake mix (do not stir). Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: southern peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in a large mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Gradually add whipped topping and powdered sugar.
Continue beating until smooth.
Spoon filling into prepared crust.
Freeze at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: won ton soup
directions: Combine chicken, cabbage, green onions and soy sauce.
Mix well and let stand approximately 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk gradually. Combine dry ingredients with eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Mix well. Blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool for 4 hours or longer.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Flour and grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt, soda and baking powder; set aside. Mix oil, eggs, pimentos, milk, corn and peppers.
Add cheese, then add dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: sausage and egg breakfast dish
directions: Place bread crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cooked meat on top of bread.
Mix milk, eggs, mustard and salt together and pour over mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli in small pieces.
Dice cheese into small chunks. Fry bacon until crisp and break into pieces.
Place broccoli, cheese and bacon into large mixing bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and oil in separate bowl (mix well).
Pour dressing on broccoli mixture; mix well.
Refrigerate to chill.
Recommend Swiss cheese.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
Add onion, mayonnaise and cheese.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop from spoon on wax paper.
